WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.325
BRIAN: What's up, GenCon?!

00:00:07.325 --> 00:00:13.896
(cheering)

00:00:13.896 --> 00:00:19.203
BRIAN: That's a lot of people. How you guys
doing?

00:00:19.203 --> 00:00:23.196
(cheering)

00:00:23.196 --> 00:00:36.127
BRIAN: Oh my god. Send me the bill for your plane
ticket! If you guys think this outfit is

00:00:36.127 --> 00:00:45.957
ridiculous, you have literally not seen anything
yet. Okay. Thank you for waiting. What?

00:00:45.957 --> 00:00:48.251
(muffled shout)

00:00:48.251 --> 00:00:55.065
BRIAN: You know what's up, brother. Thank you guys
for waiting. I heard, Tico told me that people

00:00:55.065 --> 00:01:03.155
were out there at 6:00am waiting? You guys! We're
about to watch people play Dungeons and Dragons!

00:01:03.155 --> 00:01:07.826
(cheering)

00:01:07.826 --> 00:01:15.264
BRIAN: What is happening?! We are alive at the
best moment in history. Right now, there's a

00:01:15.264 --> 00:01:21.115
stadium full of people basically watching this
live on the internet, and going,

00:01:21.115 --> 00:01:23.397
"How did Ashley let him wear that?"

00:01:23.397 --> 00:01:30.026
(laughter)

00:01:30.026 --> 00:01:43.455
BRIAN: Okay, let's start. Let's get started.
(laughs) It is I, your host for the evening,

00:01:43.455 --> 00:01:54.962
Recession-Friendly Ryan Seacrest. This outfit is
what happens when you take 'shrooms before

00:01:54.962 --> 00:01:57.166
creating a Saint's Row character.

00:01:57.166 --> 00:02:00.346
(laughter)

00:02:00.346 --> 00:02:06.661
BRIAN: All right. You guys already sound a little
warmed up.

00:02:06.661 --> 00:02:14.747
(cheering)

00:02:14.747 --> 00:02:24.374
BRIAN: Yeah. But! Just to make sure, because the
live shows are all about the audience

00:02:24.374 --> 00:02:31.836
participation. We're going to go over a couple of
rules for that really fast, but before we do, I

00:02:31.836 --> 00:02:37.106
get paid to be the hype man, so let me get you
guys hyped up.

00:02:37.106 --> 00:02:48.248
(cheering)

00:02:48.248 --> 00:02:56.749
BRIAN: Okay, wait. Okay. When I say, "Tary," you
say "Who?" Tary!

00:02:56.749 --> 00:02:57.846
AUDIENCE: Who!

00:02:57.846 --> 00:02:58.532
BRIAN: Tary!

00:02:58.532 --> 00:02:59.384
AUDIENCE: Who!

00:02:59.384 --> 00:03:02.757
BRIAN: When I say, "Tary," you say, "Who?" Tary!

00:03:02.757 --> 00:03:03.636
AUDIENCE: Who?

00:03:03.636 --> 00:03:04.419
BRIAN: Tary!

00:03:04.419 --> 00:03:05.257
AUDIENCE: Who?

00:03:05.257 --> 00:03:08.377
BRIAN: When I say, "Tary," you say "What!" Tary!

00:03:08.377 --> 00:03:09.307
AUDIENCE: What!

00:03:09.307 --> 00:03:10.136
BRAIN: Tary!

00:03:10.136 --> 00:03:11.032
AUDIENCE: What!

00:03:11.032 --> 00:03:19.758
BRAIN: Goddamn. Okay, that's it. Warm-up time
over. That was easy. Okay, here's the deal.

00:03:19.758 --> 00:03:24.707
Sometimes, people in the Twitch chat don't like
Critical Role Live because the audience

00:03:24.707 --> 00:03:40.188
participates. Those people-- (laughs) Those
people-- hold on. I just want to say, with all the

00:03:40.188 --> 00:03:44.849
love and respect in my heart, those people can
tune off right now.

00:03:44.849 --> 00:03:51.213
(cheering)

00:03:51.213 --> 00:03:55.319
BRIAN: Because I don't know about you, but when
I'm at home watching Critical Role, and someone

00:03:55.319 --> 00:03:58.537
gets a "how do you want to do this," I fucking
scream!

00:03:58.537 --> 00:04:02.618
(cheering)

00:04:02.618 --> 00:04:15.310
BRIAN: Okay. Here's what you can do. You can
laugh, you can cheer, you can scream, you can cry.

00:04:15.310 --> 00:04:22.265
You can stand up and blow the roof off this place
if something cool happens. You can hug your

00:04:22.265 --> 00:04:29.228
neighbor, and get drunk after the show if
something sad happens. And then someone please

00:04:29.228 --> 00:04:37.243
tweet me the bar that you're at, and I will join
you... with Travis Willingham's American Express.

00:04:37.243 --> 00:04:54.474
Which is currently in my fanny pack. Please do not
shout rules. Please do not shout advice. Please do

00:04:54.474 --> 00:05:05.286
not shout corrections. Please do not shout ideas.
Odds are, your idea is probably better that what

00:05:05.286 --> 00:05:12.299
some of the stuff they're going to come up with
is. However, part of the thing that is so

00:05:12.299 --> 00:05:19.236
endearing about this show is watching these
nerdy-ass voice actors figure out how to play

00:05:19.236 --> 00:05:21.171
Dungeons and Dragons.

00:05:21.171 --> 00:05:34.858
Isn't it? That's what I love about it. Okay. It's
disruptive, and it'll light the community on fire,

00:05:34.858 --> 00:05:41.151
and we like to keep these live things, but all
that being said, please laugh, please cheer.

00:05:41.151 --> 00:05:44.797
There's going to be so much cool stuff. Oh, I was
supposed to throw these out.

00:05:44.797 --> 00:06:01.490
(cheering)

00:06:01.490 --> 00:06:14.883
BRIAN: (laughs) Okay. All right. Thank you, guys.
Who came here from outside the US? Cheer.

00:06:14.883 --> 00:06:17.289
(cheering)

00:06:17.289 --> 00:06:34.917
BRIAN: Wow! Really? For this? Look at me! Without
further ado, I would like to introduce the cast of

00:06:34.917 --> 00:06:38.248
a little show we like to call Critical Role.

00:06:38.248 --> 00:07:02.317
Travis Willingham!

00:07:02.317 --> 00:07:17.319
Laura Bailey!

00:07:17.319 --> 00:07:31.629
Liam O'Brien!

00:07:31.629 --> 00:07:44.008
Marisha Ray!

00:07:44.008 --> 00:07:58.358
Taliesin Jaffe!

00:07:58.358 --> 00:08:40.569
Children, shield your eyes. I present to you: Sam
Riegel!

00:08:40.569 --> 00:09:03.101
And the man that brought us all together. Ladies
and gentlemen, Matthew Mercer!

00:09:03.101 --> 00:09:07.455
The cast of Critical Role, ladies and gentlemen!

00:09:07.455 --> 00:09:23.302
(cheering)

00:09:23.302 --> 00:09:24.237
TRAVIS: All right.

00:09:24.237 --> 00:09:28.180
LAURA: All right.

00:09:28.180 --> 00:09:31.416
TRAVIS: Fuck! Fucking shit!

00:09:31.416 --> 00:09:59.406
(cheering)

00:09:59.406 --> 00:10:08.081
MATT: So that's surreal. Oh man. Well, we're all
so excited for you guys to join us tonight, both

00:10:08.081 --> 00:10:13.713
here in person and out there on the internet. How
crazy is it that we live in a world where, right

00:10:13.713 --> 00:10:17.615
now, we have people here live in this fantastic
theater to watch Dungeons and Dragons?

00:10:17.615 --> 00:10:28.661
(cheering)

00:10:28.661 --> 00:10:34.870
MATT: For all the crazy shit going on in the
world, it's nice to know that we can carve some

00:10:34.870 --> 00:10:36.779
good out of it here tonight.

00:10:36.779 --> 00:10:42.933
(cheering)

00:10:42.933 --> 00:10:45.359
MATT: And in that regard, so we don't keep you too
long before we can get to the game which you all

00:10:45.359 --> 00:10:54.712
came here to watch, let's go through some quick
announcements. Very quick. In fact, I think the

00:10:54.712 --> 00:10:57.420
big announcement, if Liam and Taliesin want to
take that?

00:10:57.420 --> 00:11:10.036
LIAM: Sure. So Taliesin and I have been working on
something for about a year, with around 89 artists

00:11:10.036 --> 00:11:22.458
from our community. It's been a glimmer in our eye
for over a year, and it is almost here. We're

00:11:22.458 --> 00:11:27.906
going to be releasing, in the fall from the Geek &amp;amp;
Sundry store, a Critical Role art book.

00:11:27.906 --> 00:11:50.400
(cheering)

00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:55.162
SAM: Liam, they're excited about reading. They
love books!

00:11:55.162 --> 00:11:58.302
TALIESIN: We've only told them about the pictures
so far.

00:11:58.302 --> 00:12:03.805
LIAM: You guys know what a crucial part of this
community the artists have become, and we have

00:12:03.805 --> 00:12:10.883
selected 89 artists from many more; there wasn't
enough-- pages are limited, do I have a page

00:12:10.883 --> 00:12:11.963
number on here?

00:12:11.963 --> 00:12:15.115
TALIESIN: 260 something pages?

00:12:15.115 --> 00:12:17.044
BRIAN: 256, Liam!

00:12:17.044 --> 00:12:18.951
TALIESIN: 256 pages.

00:12:18.951 --> 00:12:29.129
LIAM: We've seen it, and it is beautiful. There's
going to be a deluxe edition and a standard

00:12:29.129 --> 00:12:36.164
edition. It will be available for sale in the Geek
&amp;amp; Sundry store in the late fall, published by

00:12:36.164 --> 00:12:37.492
Hunters Books.

00:12:37.492 --> 00:12:48.278
TALIESIN: I'll say, regardless of what version,
when you actually get the book, it's going to be

00:12:48.278 --> 00:12:57.245
treated as an artifact from the Cobalt Reserve, so
there's going to be historical texts and writings

00:12:57.245 --> 00:13:04.390
from various librarians in the Cobalt Reserve,
chronicling the adventures of Vox Machina,

00:13:04.390 --> 00:13:18.099
including a lot of fun Easter eggs. And there will
be some fun Easter eggs in there, there may even

00:13:18.099 --> 00:13:21.354
be some background meta data that doesn't really
exist anywhere else.

00:13:21.354 --> 00:13:27.358
LIAM: Yeah. This is not your basic, go the CVS
store and get a photo book made. A lot of love and

00:13:27.358 --> 00:13:34.218
care went into this. We've been talking with
artists for months and months. A lot of blood,

00:13:34.218 --> 00:13:37.223
sweat and tears have gone into this. We're very
grateful to the artists who are involved, some of

00:13:37.223 --> 00:13:38.944
them are in this audience tonight; thank you.

00:13:38.944 --> 00:13:52.148
(cheering)

00:13:52.148 --> 00:13:57.631
LIAM: We stood around and looked at a proof of
this about a week ago, and I might have gotten a

00:13:57.631 --> 00:14:03.924
little verklempt. It is really special. So keep
your eyes open for it. Oh yeah, one last thing. To

00:14:03.924 --> 00:14:09.045
keep up to date, I'm sure we'll talk more about
it, but you can visit geekandsundry.com/artbook to

00:14:09.045 --> 00:14:12.295
sign up for email updates and book previews, so do
so.

00:14:12.295 --> 00:14:20.037
TALIESIN: It should be available for ordering
sometime in the late fall.

00:14:20.037 --> 00:14:23.907
ALL: Late fall!

00:14:23.907 --> 00:14:25.541
MATT: Thank you guys very much.

00:14:25.541 --> 00:14:26.947
LAURA: Yeah, thank you guys.

00:14:26.947 --> 00:14:30.386
MATT: These two busted their ass on this book.

00:14:30.386 --> 00:14:39.052
(cheering)

00:14:39.052 --> 00:14:56.977
MATT: The other quick announcement we have: it's a
fun little thing that'll be tomorrow for those of

00:14:56.977 --> 00:14:59.954
us at GenCon, and if it goes over well hopefully
at other events in future, but when we released

00:14:59.954 --> 00:15:10.157
the Tal'Dorei campaign guide, the original design
of the cover was from a POV of Scanlan, and there

00:15:10.157 --> 00:15:16.575
was some dissent in the community that Scanlan
wasn't in full display on the cover. So I

00:15:16.575 --> 00:15:21.025
contacted Aaron Riley, the fantastic artist that
worked on our cover, and we got some vinyl decals

00:15:21.025 --> 00:15:31.548
made so you can put one of two different pictures
of Scanlan on your cover of the book or any book

00:15:31.548 --> 00:15:33.108
or art piece you find.

00:15:33.108 --> 00:15:41.092
(cheering)

00:15:41.092 --> 00:15:45.491
MATT: We're hoping to have those in tomorrow, for
those who can come to the signing, and even if you

00:15:45.491 --> 00:15:48.716
didn't get a ticket for the signing, come to the
event anyway. We will have those available to pass

00:15:48.716 --> 00:15:53.531
out, hopefully. So you can pick from the two, or
grab one of each, it's going to be ridiculous. One

00:15:53.531 --> 00:15:55.386
of the particular images, I'm excited to see where
Scanlan shows up.

00:15:55.386 --> 00:15:56.827
LAURA: They're really great.

00:15:56.827 --> 00:15:57.970
MATT: It's absurd.

00:15:57.970 --> 00:15:59.970
LIAM: Why's this small man on the Sistine Chapel?

00:15:59.970 --> 00:16:04.600
(laughter)

00:16:04.600 --> 00:16:10.545
MATT: That's why they're vinyl; you can remove
them without damaging property. I think. We'll

00:16:10.545 --> 00:16:14.451
find out. Anyway, without further ado, I think
that brings us to the end of our announcements for

00:16:14.451 --> 00:16:23.296
the evening, and as such, bring us into tonight's
episode of Critical Role.

00:16:23.296 --> 00:17:51.963
[dramatic music]

00:17:51.963 --> 00:18:02.238
TRAVIS: Let's go!

00:18:02.238 --> 00:18:05.524
MATT: All right, let's bring this down.

00:18:05.524 --> 00:18:09.271
MARISHA: Holy shit.

00:18:09.271 --> 00:18:12.472
LIAM: Vecna's Amish taint.

00:18:12.472 --> 00:18:15.315
(laughter)

00:18:15.315 --> 00:18:22.531
MATT: A little late, but thank you. I appreciate
that. Last we left off, Vox Machina, in their trek

00:18:22.531 --> 00:18:28.354
to eventually hopefully seal and be rid of the
threat of Vecna, the Whispered One, in his

00:18:28.354 --> 00:18:33.449
recently ascended godhood on the Prime Material
Plane, found themselves traversing below the

00:18:33.449 --> 00:18:41.487
sub-ocean volcano, the Scaldseat, where they
managed to water-breathe their way through a jug.

00:18:41.487 --> 00:18:52.773
They traversed the poisonous air within, and
coming upon the Allhammer's Core Anvil, on which

00:18:52.773 --> 00:18:58.869
many artifacts of the Founding and beyond were
forged. There, you fought with the forge guardian,

00:18:58.869 --> 00:19:04.255
who was left to see who has proven worthy to
utilize its components. You defeated it, and in

00:19:04.255 --> 00:19:10.908
doing so, Percival, with the designs bestowed upon
you from Ioun, and Grog, with the bestowed-upon

00:19:10.908 --> 00:19:16.512
knowledge of blacksmithing, took to the blacksmith
tools and together managed to forge, barely

00:19:16.512 --> 00:19:25.188
successfully with a modicum of structural
integrity, the three Prime Trammels, hopefully

00:19:25.188 --> 00:19:30.161
intended to destroy-- or at least seal off--
Vecna's influence on this plane.

00:19:30.161 --> 00:19:38.781
The trammels now complete, each glowing with the
runes of each gifted deity power source. We have

00:19:38.781 --> 00:19:43.579
one that glows yellow across its runic outside,
one that is a sky blue, and one that emanates a

00:19:43.579 --> 00:19:47.976
black shadow from its runes, representing each
deity that bequeathed an element of their power

00:19:47.976 --> 00:19:55.311
unto these trammels. You then decided to have
Scanlan drop his magnificent mansion and decide

00:19:55.311 --> 00:20:00.130
where your next journey was. As you all enter the
mansion, preparing for an evening's rest or

00:20:00.130 --> 00:20:05.896
otherwise, we left off with you, now, away from
the heat of the volcano, plotting your next

00:20:05.896 --> 00:20:07.520
directional path.

00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:10.223
So Vox Machina, what do you want to do?

00:20:10.223 --> 00:20:12.463
LIAM: That's a great question.

00:20:12.463 --> 00:20:15.654
LAURA: Let me see those trammels. Who has the
trammels?

00:20:15.654 --> 00:20:17.029
TRAVIS: I do. Why?

00:20:17.029 --> 00:20:18.431
LAURA: I just want to look at them.

00:20:18.431 --> 00:20:19.596
TRAVIS: All of them or just one?

00:20:19.596 --> 00:20:21.036
LAURA: All of them.

00:20:21.036 --> 00:20:22.724
TRAVIS: Fucking hell, shit. Here you go.

00:20:22.724 --> 00:20:25.787
LAURA: That's it. I just want to hold them,
really.

00:20:25.787 --> 00:20:28.643
TRAVIS: They're real big, right?

00:20:28.643 --> 00:20:32.740
LAURA: Yeah, I'm cradling them, Grog.

00:20:32.740 --> 00:20:36.236
MATT: Surprisingly, though, due to the platinum's
design, they're not as heavy as you expect them,

00:20:36.236 --> 00:20:39.414
whether it'd be the enchantment or the material
that it was made from. They're still heavy for

00:20:39.414 --> 00:20:42.302
you, Vex, because your strength is pretty shitty.

00:20:42.302 --> 00:20:48.431
LAURA: Can I tell which one is which god?

00:20:48.431 --> 00:20:53.158
MATT: Yes. The one that glows yellow, you feel a
slight bit of kinship with the blessing you

00:20:53.158 --> 00:20:58.035
received from Pelor, the Dawnfather. The other
two, you can differentiate being the sky blue

00:20:58.035 --> 00:21:02.473
color, probably with Ioun, the Knowing Mistress,
and the black probably representing the Raven

00:21:02.473 --> 00:21:04.072
Queen.

00:21:04.072 --> 00:21:07.876
LAURA: All right, cool, I'm going to hold on to
the Pelor one. Pass them back.

00:21:07.876 --> 00:21:09.271
TRAVIS: I've got the other two?

00:21:09.271 --> 00:21:11.639
LAURA: Yeah. I don't know if anybody else wants to
hold one.

00:21:11.639 --> 00:21:16.082
TRAVIS: Just in case things go sour I also thought of
a nice way to use these, and I slide one between

00:21:16.082 --> 00:21:27.755
each of my fingers, and I hold it up. (shink)
Okay, back in the Bag of Holding.

00:21:27.755 --> 00:21:30.805
LIAM: Are you still embiggened right now?

00:21:30.805 --> 00:21:32.782
TRAVIS: No, I haven't been biggened for a while.

00:21:32.782 --> 00:21:35.782
LAURA: Yeah, he was only big fighting the
bulette.

00:21:35.782 --> 00:21:45.322
TRAVIS: Oh, wait. By the way, I believe you said
that if I successfully did all of these trammels

00:21:45.322 --> 00:21:53.183
that you had something for me. Thought I wouldn't
remember, did you?

00:21:53.183 --> 00:21:57.854
(laughter)

00:21:57.854 --> 00:22:05.123
LIAM: I did say that. It's rather personal,
though, I hope the rest of you can understand

00:22:05.123 --> 00:22:08.762
that. I'm not going to be around for much longer,
so I wanted to say--

00:22:08.762 --> 00:22:11.608
SAM: Do you want us to step out so you can have a
moment?

00:22:11.608 --> 00:22:13.844
LIAM: No, we'll find a minute.

00:22:13.844 --> 00:22:16.872
SAM: What? What does that mean?

00:22:16.872 --> 00:22:22.283
LIAM: It's awkward; it's not something I'm
comfortable talking with--

00:22:22.283 --> 00:22:24.218
LAURA: So you want us to leave?

00:22:24.218 --> 00:22:30.508
LIAM: No! We can talk out a plan. Tonight before
we go to bed. It could be now; it could be later.

00:22:30.508 --> 00:22:33.717
MARISHA: You've said too much about it now.

00:22:33.717 --> 00:22:39.420
LIAM: I take Grog by the arm, and I usher him out
the door of the mansion.

00:22:39.420 --> 00:22:40.854
TRAVIS: This is weird.

00:22:40.854 --> 00:22:43.792
LAURA: Outside the mansion? You're out the mansion
now?

00:22:43.792 --> 00:22:44.781
LIAM:Yeah.

00:22:44.781 --> 00:22:46.423
SAM: You're going outside?

00:22:46.423 --> 00:22:47.762
LIAM: Just out the front door.

00:22:47.762 --> 00:22:49.938
SAM: Into the inside of the volcano?

00:22:49.938 --> 00:22:51.148
LIAM: Is it on fire?

00:22:51.148 --> 00:22:52.850
MATT: It's certainly very hot.

00:22:52.850 --> 00:22:57.517
LIAM: Fuck it, Grog, let's go downstairs.

00:22:57.517 --> 00:22:59.179
TRAVIS: War room!

00:22:59.179 --> 00:23:00.789
MARISHA: He has 40 floors!

00:23:00.789 --> 00:23:03.123
TRAVIS: We're going down to the war room, which is
a sand pit.

00:23:03.123 --> 00:23:06.041
LIAM: Yeah, and I ignore all of the cat-calling
and all of the sniping and all of the shittiness.

00:23:06.041 --> 00:23:07.522
These fucking assholes.

00:23:07.522 --> 00:23:10.192
LAURA: Have fun, you two!

00:23:10.192 --> 00:23:11.867
SAM: Use protection!

00:23:11.867 --> 00:23:19.090
(laughter)

00:23:19.090 --> 00:23:23.384
LIAM: That's what Grog is for!

00:23:23.384 --> 00:23:27.227
MATT: The two of you descend the staircase into
the subterranean war room, where there you see

00:23:27.227 --> 00:23:30.727
before you the giant sand pit that is currently
adorned with multiple training dummies with armor

00:23:30.727 --> 00:23:36.169
and weapons. Strapped to them, magnificently
pristine, based on how many times you destroyed

00:23:36.169 --> 00:23:39.454
and/or restructured the chamber, but there it lies
before you.

00:23:39.454 --> 00:23:41.578
LIAM: Big man?

00:23:41.578 --> 00:23:43.023
TRAVIS: Yeah? That's me.

00:23:43.023 --> 00:23:54.366
LIAM: I'm not going to be around much longer,
probably, or you're not going to be around much

00:23:54.366 --> 00:23:55.802
longer; one or the other.

00:23:55.802 --> 00:23:56.784
