01:06:56.398 --> 01:07:00.370
MARISHA: Okay, you know what? Don't worry about
it, let's go. Let's just Plane Shift.

01:07:00.370 --> 01:07:02.937
MATT: That's an arduous journey back to any
possible tree.

01:07:02.937 --> 01:07:05.093
TRAVIS: Wanted to talk that one out.

01:07:05.093 --> 01:07:08.395
MARISHA: Yeah. I Plane Shift us to Vasselheim.

01:07:08.395 --> 01:07:13.648
MATT: All right, so you Plane Shift to Vasselheim.
As you guys encircle your hands once more,

01:07:13.648 --> 01:07:15.848
Keyleth, you focus on whereabouts in Vasselheim?

01:07:15.848 --> 01:07:17.117
TRAVIS: The Trial Forge?

01:07:17.117 --> 01:07:22.284
LAURA: Or Melora's tree maybe?

01:07:22.284 --> 01:07:39.651
(laughter and applause)

01:07:39.688 --> 01:07:42.616
SAM: Residual magic.

01:07:42.616 --> 01:07:47.949
TRAVIS, SAM, and TALIESIN: Trial Forge?

01:07:47.949 --> 01:07:50.558
MARISHA: Where will you not get arrested?

01:07:50.558 --> 01:08:00.501
TRAVIS: No one's going to even notice me. Yeah,
they were ringing the bells and running around and

01:08:00.501 --> 01:08:08.248
getting prepared and stuff. Yeah, and if for some
reason, somebody's like, "That guy punched me in

01:08:08.248 --> 01:08:10.995
"the face," we'll just punch them.

01:08:10.995 --> 01:08:15.046
TALIESIN: I agree with this plan.

01:08:15.046 --> 01:08:16.279
MARISHA: Trial Forge.

01:08:16.279 --> 01:08:22.858
MATT: All right. With that, you close your eyes.
Beneath your breath, you recite the incantation.

01:08:22.858 --> 01:08:29.509
With that, you feel your body suddenly sucked into
a dark void and thrust through the absence of

01:08:29.509 --> 01:08:34.794
space. And within a moment's time, before you can
adjust to the sudden cold and dark vacuous void

01:08:34.794 --> 01:08:41.185
around you, your feet hit hard ground, your eyes
focus again to the light, and you glance around

01:08:41.185 --> 01:08:50.136
and the center streets, not actually directly at
the Trial Forge-- ooh, we got music, finally. In

01:08:50.136 --> 01:08:55.598
the streets around the Braving Grounds, you can
see the smokestacks from the Trial Forge over the

01:08:55.598 --> 01:09:06.278
distance. You also notice that the sky above you
is deep, dark gray clouds. It's as if there is a

01:09:06.278 --> 01:09:11.427
perpetual eclipse placed upon this ground. You
look around in all directions, and you see this

01:09:11.427 --> 01:09:19.452
roiling gray cloud cluster that encompasses the
entirety of the sky above you, which should be

01:09:19.452 --> 01:09:27.640
mid-morning or midday. It's blotted out by the
storm-- rainfall is absent-- and you see flashes

01:09:27.640 --> 01:09:34.146
of light, occasionally framing strange shapes
and clouds. Whether by illusion or by a trick of

01:09:34.146 --> 01:09:43.548
your mind, you swear you see shifting darkness and
forms, images in the clouds: giant faces silently

01:09:43.590 --> 01:09:51.266
screaming, hundreds of feet across, that extend and
push out of the clouds and draw back into the sky.

01:09:51.311 --> 01:09:57.208
Massive hands that push against them, only to
slowly recede moments later. You blink and they're

01:09:57.208 --> 01:10:01.487
gone, leaving you unsettled regardless and
uncertain as to whether or not that was just you

01:10:01.487 --> 01:10:04.512
or if everyone can see this.

01:10:04.512 --> 01:10:09.617
As your focus shifts from the sky above, you look
around and you can see Bastions are stationed all

01:10:09.617 --> 01:10:16.186
across the perimeter walls of Vasselheim. You see
large ballistae mounted and armed as watchers

01:10:16.186 --> 01:10:21.628
scour the distant horizon on all sides looking for
any sign of something in the distance making its

01:10:21.628 --> 01:10:27.175
way towards the city, based on the warning you
previously gave. Unlit beacons sit at every major

01:10:27.175 --> 01:10:32.029
structure and juncture of the stone walls,
awaiting the burning sign that an assault is

01:10:32.029 --> 01:10:39.078
spotted. Militia and armored guard move with haste
to stations across the city quarters. You can feel

01:10:39.078 --> 01:10:42.932
the air of war permeating the streets.

01:10:42.932 --> 01:10:47.647
The streets are far emptier than you recall, the
stragglers returning to their homes with carts

01:10:47.647 --> 01:10:55.513
full of rations, produce, and weapons. Fear grips
their face as they pass by. You glance off to your

01:10:55.513 --> 01:11:01.378
left, and you can see a wiry old man in the
corner, his tangled silver and blond hair

01:11:01.378 --> 01:11:07.881
bouncing with fervor, as he shouts out, "The
reckoning of our opulence has come! The gods are

01:11:07.881 --> 01:11:13.098
"away and the price of our hubris comes to consume
us." But no one's paying him mind. His tattered

01:11:13.098 --> 01:11:18.373
bones jangling his knees across each other, as he
makes his way through the streets, his face a

01:11:18.373 --> 01:11:21.215
glance of utter despair.

01:11:21.215 --> 01:11:27.408
You notice an argument between two Bastions and a
middle-aged bearded man who is painting a familiar

01:11:27.408 --> 01:11:31.946
symbol on his front door, not too far from where
you stand. A five-year-old girl cries and clings

01:11:31.946 --> 01:11:35.886
to his leg. What do you do?

01:11:35.886 --> 01:11:38.835
TALIESIN: What is the symbol?

01:11:38.835 --> 01:11:41.271
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:11:41.271 --> 01:11:45.719
TALIESIN: I'll make a perception check. Let's see
if you'll roll a one again. No, that's much

01:11:45.719 --> 01:11:49.702
better. 28.

01:11:49.702 --> 01:11:57.479
MATT: Glancing at this distance, you see a
familiar and striking shape. It is a haphazardly

01:11:57.479 --> 01:12:05.531
drawn circle with dark, reddish purple paint and
a small line and a pronged fork of four prongs

01:12:05.531 --> 01:12:08.005
painted up against this wall.

01:12:08.005 --> 01:12:09.545
MARISHA: Oh, hell no.

01:12:09.545 --> 01:12:12.253
LAURA: He's painting it on the door? The guy in
the city is?

01:12:12.253 --> 01:12:14.554
MATT: The father figure.

01:12:14.554 --> 01:12:17.049
LIAM: Yeah. It could be to pass over their house.

01:12:17.049 --> 01:12:18.045
TALIESIN: Yes.

01:12:18.045 --> 01:12:19.918
MARISHA: Pass over?

01:12:19.918 --> 01:12:21.884
LAURA: That's the Vecna symbol, right?

01:12:21.884 --> 01:12:27.727
MATT: Sensing the distance of Vecna, he's still
far to the northwest of here. But what was once a

01:12:27.727 --> 01:12:38.432
few hundred miles is now shortened, about two
hundred or so, and getting lesser and lesser.

01:12:38.432 --> 01:12:41.067
LAURA: Fuck. Should we go up and talk to that
guy?

01:12:41.067 --> 01:12:45.303
MARISHA: Maybe one of us. Maybe not all of us.

01:12:45.303 --> 01:12:46.423
LAURA: You there.

01:12:46.423 --> 01:12:52.410
MATT: As you make the shout, you see the soldiers
are currently arguing with him. One says, "You

01:12:52.410 --> 01:12:55.746
"welcome this rubbish? Are you one of them kook
believers?"

01:12:55.746 --> 01:13:02.283
And the father is angrily staring in his face and
says, "You mind your business. I have no love for

01:13:02.283 --> 01:13:05.121
"this, but if these dreams are true, I must protect
my family."

01:13:05.121 --> 01:13:06.887
LAURA: Dreams?

01:13:06.887 --> 01:13:08.999
MATT: They turn and look at you as you approach.

01:13:08.999 --> 01:13:10.961
LAURA: What dreams?

01:13:10.961 --> 01:13:15.430
MATT: The soldiers take a step back with a look of
recognition across you as you step forward with

01:13:15.430 --> 01:13:22.319
your white dragon scale armor. They know not to
approach and there is seemingly a sense of knowing

01:13:22.319 --> 01:13:27.539
who you are, at least from the legends that are
told amongst the streets of Vasselheim. The father

01:13:27.539 --> 01:13:35.676
turns to you and seeing your lordly approach, and
strong voice, immediately. "The nightmares I've

01:13:35.676 --> 01:13:47.317
"had, and I'm not the first. This symbol. It scares
me, but if something comes like they say it is, I

01:13:47.317 --> 01:13:51.896
"must it let it know we have no quarrel. To
leave my family be."

01:13:51.896 --> 01:13:54.603
LAURA: This symbol will not protect you.

01:13:54.603 --> 01:13:55.944
MATT: "How do you know this?"

01:13:55.944 --> 01:14:04.302
LAURA: Because I know his followers. They won't
have mercy. They'll gouge out eyes, remove your

01:14:04.302 --> 01:14:07.277
hand, and make you one of them.

01:14:07.277 --> 01:14:09.109
MATT: Make a persuasion check, please.

01:14:09.109 --> 01:14:19.465
LAURA: Okay. Hold on. 17?

01:14:19.465 --> 01:14:29.018
MATT: Okay, he looks at you for a moment, his eyes
keen with fear, and his face. "You're certain of

01:14:29.018 --> 01:14:30.327
"this, my lady?"

01:14:30.327 --> 01:14:32.106
LAURA: Yes.

01:14:32.106 --> 01:14:35.545
MATT: "Will you protect us, then?"

01:14:35.545 --> 01:14:39.165
LAURA: We'll do our best. That's what we're here
for.

01:14:39.165 --> 01:14:45.054
MATT: He looks past you, the rest of your
companions, all looking well-armed and definitely

01:14:45.054 --> 01:14:52.963
capable. Looks down and rubs the hair of his
little girl, her sandy blonde hair curled up and a

01:14:52.963 --> 01:15:02.355
bit dirtied. Looking down from her gaze, up to
you, he says, "Then I trust you." He takes the

01:15:02.355 --> 01:15:06.139
tattered paintbrush he was using and smears across
the symbol, destroying it.

01:15:06.139 --> 01:15:16.248
(applause)

01:15:16.248 --> 01:15:18.895
LAURA: Dear god, I hope that works.

01:15:18.895 --> 01:15:28.675
MATT: He goes inside with his daughter. Before he
closes the door: "Thank you. Please, help." Pulls

01:15:28.675 --> 01:15:31.495
the rest of the cart in and closes the door behind
with a slam.

01:15:31.495 --> 01:15:37.834
The two guards awkwardly look at each other and
back to you. "Thank you."

01:15:37.834 --> 01:15:50.745
(laughter)

01:15:50.745 --> 01:15:53.806
MATT: "Be safe." And they both wander off.

01:15:53.806 --> 01:15:56.676
LAURA: I don't think they noticed you, Grog.

01:15:56.676 --> 01:15:59.035
TRAVIS: Man, I'm fucking slick.

01:15:59.035 --> 01:16:06.723
MATT: Knowing the location, you're not that far
from the Quadroads juncture between the different

01:16:06.723 --> 01:16:12.194
areas. You can go further towards the Trial Forge
or back towards the center of where the Quadroads

01:16:12.194 --> 01:16:17.180
meets between that and where the Platinum
Sanctuary and Platinum Dragon section is. There is

01:16:17.180 --> 01:16:23.950
the temple to Sarenrae, where you left Pike
previously. What do you wish to do?

01:16:23.950 --> 01:16:27.734
MARISHA: Is the crazy zealot still running
around?

01:16:27.734 --> 01:16:32.211
MATT: Yeah. He seems to be scattered through the
streets. He's maybe 60 feet away, still shouting

01:16:32.211 --> 01:16:35.608
obscenities and weird doom-saying prophecies.

01:16:35.608 --> 01:16:37.627
MARISHA: I walk up to him.

01:16:37.627 --> 01:16:45.359
MATT: Okay. As he's shouting this time, "He will
come! He will destroy us! You! He will destroy

01:16:45.359 --> 01:16:48.589
"you, too! I've seen it! I've seen it."

01:16:48.589 --> 01:16:51.942
MARISHA: Yeah. I believe you. I've seen it, too.

01:16:51.942 --> 01:16:56.917
MATT: "Good! Then save yourself! Run! Run far!"

01:16:56.917 --> 01:17:00.487
MARISHA: Wait. How did he talk to you?

01:17:00.487 --> 01:17:09.062
MATT: "In my mind. In my dreams. He comes. He says
it's inevitable. The clouds, they come as the

01:17:09.062 --> 01:17:13.628
"first warning. The first seal broken. The sky has
already left us. The sun is gone!"

01:17:13.628 --> 01:17:20.672
MARISHA: Okay. Yeah, no. Accurate.

01:17:20.672 --> 01:17:33.416
MATT: "Beware the Undying King!" And he goes to
run off, away.

01:17:33.416 --> 01:17:35.499
LAURA: Is he already gone?

01:17:35.499 --> 01:17:37.228
MATT: He's running away.

01:17:37.228 --> 01:17:40.423
MARISHA: Man, I don't know how to deal with that
type of abrasive personality.

01:17:40.423 --> 01:17:47.651
LAURA: Maybe it's best to not let people give him
power, because the more people believe in him, the

01:17:47.651 --> 01:17:49.197
stronger of a god he becomes.

01:17:49.197 --> 01:17:56.286
MARISHA: But that guy resisted. He knew when
others didn't. And he was crazy.

01:17:56.286 --> 01:18:01.037
LAURA: Could you maybe make the sun reappear?

01:18:01.037 --> 01:18:12.715
MARISHA: I don't know. Can I do a nature check to
see if this is above my capabilities?

01:18:12.715 --> 01:18:21.667
MATT: It's definitely an unnatural form of weather
pattern. You get the sense that this is itself a

01:18:21.667 --> 01:18:23.178
minor miracle.

01:18:23.178 --> 01:18:25.134
MARISHA: A minor miracle?

01:18:25.134 --> 01:18:30.961
MATT: Well, yeah. The sky that stretches beyond
all sides of the horizon is of similar strange,

01:18:30.961 --> 01:18:33.481
roiling cloud doom.

01:18:33.481 --> 01:18:35.527
LAURA: Is it like Ghostbusters?

01:18:35.527 --> 01:18:41.206
MATT: It's very similar, yeah. We're talking top
of the tower, curling ink clouds out to each side,

01:18:41.206 --> 01:18:47.144
traveling with vast speed in almost all
directions. You see no plain, single path in which

01:18:47.144 --> 01:18:49.110
they're traveling. They're emanating.

01:18:49.110 --> 01:18:52.512
MARISHA: This seems like a minor miracle.

01:18:52.512 --> 01:18:56.638
LAURA: Yeah. Can you miracle more?

01:18:56.638 --> 01:19:06.526
MARISHA: I could maybe try to carve out a patch of
sunlight above us, but I don't think it would be

01:19:06.526 --> 01:19:09.260
anything more than a morale boost, at this point.

01:19:09.260 --> 01:19:11.027
TALIESIN: If we did it at a temple, perhaps.

01:19:11.027 --> 01:19:13.180
LAURA: Maybe above the Sarenrae temple.

01:19:13.180 --> 01:19:16.650
LIAM: He's bearing down on us. We need to tell
Pike. We need to warn the authorities. We need to

01:19:16.650 --> 01:19:19.368
tell the Temple of Bahamut, the Slayer's Take.

01:19:19.368 --> 01:19:25.408
MARISHA: We have to keep people from defecting to
him. The more people that he has, the more of his

01:19:25.408 --> 01:19:30.374
symbols that get spread around out of fear, the
more he'll win.

01:19:30.374 --> 01:19:35.897
TRAVIS: Right, but we can only either spread the
word that we're going to resist or spread the word

01:19:35.897 --> 01:19:38.869
that it's about time to fight. We can only do one
or the other.

01:19:38.869 --> 01:19:41.422
LIAM: He's coming, one way or another.

01:19:41.422 --> 01:19:44.626
MARISHA: I turn to one of the guards of
Vasselheim.

01:19:44.626 --> 01:19:47.992
MATT: One of them's rushing past. He has a cluster
of spears under one arm.

01:19:47.992 --> 01:19:49.086
MARISHA: Sir!

01:19:49.086 --> 01:19:50.230
MATT: "Yes?"

01:19:50.230 --> 01:19:56.280
MARISHA: If there was a universal sign of
Vasselheim, a symbol of Vasselheim, or a sign to

01:19:56.280 --> 01:19:58.697
fight, what would it be?

01:19:58.697 --> 01:20:06.243
(laughter)

01:20:06.243 --> 01:20:14.776
MATT: "There is no universal symbol. There are
many symbols in Vasselheim. All the various

01:20:14.776 --> 01:20:17.333
"divinities that lie here have their own symbol."

01:20:17.333 --> 01:20:23.272
MARISHA: Okay. I didn't know if there was like a
rally or cry or something that you all universally

01:20:23.272 --> 01:20:28.561
believed in. There's got to be something, a symbol
of Vasselheim.

01:20:28.561 --> 01:20:31.627
MATT: "Vasselheim is a divided and united city as
one."

01:20:31.627 --> 01:20:36.552
MARISHA: All right, you know what? Never mind!
Jeez, your politics.

01:20:36.552 --> 01:20:51.263
MATT: He gives a strange glint of a glare towards
your larger goliath friend. Right as he begins to

01:20:51.263 --> 01:20:57.158
squint, you hear a voice in the distance go,
"Lieutenant, we need you!"

01:20:57.158 --> 01:20:59.651
"Right away." And he rushes off with spears under
his arm.

01:20:59.651 --> 01:21:08.657
MARISHA: Thanks, Lieutenant, for nothing. Okay,
maybe some sort of sign will help them.

01:21:08.657 --> 01:21:12.227
TALIESIN: If we're going to make a sun appear--

01:21:12.227 --> 01:21:14.268
LAURA: Let's do it at the temple of Sarenrae or
the temple of Pelor.

01:21:14.268 --> 01:21:16.283
MARISHA: All right, we go to the temple of
Sarenrae!

01:21:16.283 --> 01:21:22.108
MATT: You make your way to the temple. You enter
the interior, and you can see most everyone is in

01:21:22.108 --> 01:21:28.906
silent prayer. They're all either holding hands or
clutching close their smaller kin, these renewed

01:21:28.906 --> 01:21:38.737
worshippers of the Everlight. Glancing around, you
don't see Pike currently in the vicinity. All you

01:21:38.737 --> 01:21:43.801
see is one of the head priests, Coraline, who's
currently off to the side is tending to a few of

01:21:43.801 --> 01:21:48.109
the folks from the interior.

01:21:48.109 --> 01:21:49.460
LIAM: (shouting) Pike?

01:21:49.460 --> 01:21:54.700
MATT: Coraline looks over and sees you guys enter.
"Oh!" Rushes up to you. "I'm sorry, she's not

01:21:54.700 --> 01:22:00.748
"here, she went to the Platinum Sanctuary.
Apparently, there's a discussion, a meeting of

01:22:00.748 --> 01:22:02.122
"some kind."

01:22:02.122 --> 01:22:03.107
MARISHA: Right now?

01:22:03.107 --> 01:22:04.885
MATT: "Right now. She left not but an hour ago."

01:22:04.885 --> 01:22:05.809
MARISHA: Okay, go!

01:22:05.809 --> 01:22:06.819
LIAM: Thank you.

01:22:06.819 --> 01:22:07.948
MATT: "Of course."

01:22:07.948 --> 01:22:17.609
(laughter)

01:22:17.609 --> 01:22:23.624
MATT: Walking up the endless stair along the side of
the mountain that signifies the northern end of

01:22:23.624 --> 01:22:28.870
Vasselheim, you see small units of silver and blue
armored warriors of the Platinum Dragon descend

01:22:28.870 --> 01:22:34.332
past you, rushing and giving you a sidelong glance
as they do. A nod of recognition as some of them

01:22:34.332 --> 01:22:36.962
recognize you upon your approach.

01:22:36.962 --> 01:22:43.192
Eventually, through an exhausting ascent and
seeing the clouds growing darker and darker, you

01:22:43.192 --> 01:22:47.445
begin to see that there is, from this vantage
point, a very slight shift in their direction.

01:22:47.445 --> 01:22:50.756
They seem to be coming from the northwest.

01:22:50.756 --> 01:22:57.761
You eventually reach the base of the massive
pillars that mark the stronghold's entrance, where

01:22:57.761 --> 01:23:03.868
you've been a number of times before. You
immediately notice a crowd of mixed attire. You

01:23:03.868 --> 01:23:11.910
see Scalebearers standing tensely along various
Bastion members. You see warriors of the Dawn Fist

01:23:11.910 --> 01:23:20.403
in their gold and red robes. And you see soldiers
of brass and sapphire: the Hand of Ord is here, as

01:23:20.403 --> 01:23:31.979
well. Now, upon approaching the guards. The guards
at the front gate see you and expectantly signify

01:23:31.979 --> 01:23:39.368
for the gates to open with a shifting (thudding).
The two large marble doorways open inside, just

01:23:39.368 --> 01:23:41.889
enough for you to pass within.

01:23:41.889 --> 01:23:47.361
You enter the central chambers, the inner sanctum
of the Platinum Sanctuary, where the marble halls

01:23:47.361 --> 01:23:53.908
lead to the familiar circular forum chambers where
you last met with the Highbearer Vord, the

01:23:53.908 --> 01:24:02.025
Silver-Touched, who stands there before you, among
his guard, in heated discussion. The room is

01:24:02.025 --> 01:24:06.620
lively with representatives of each temple
clustered behind their highest lord. The red-robed

01:24:06.620 --> 01:24:14.610
Dawn Fist of Kord flank Earthbreaker Groon.
Philosophers gather near Holy Curator Curtis Uleas

01:24:14.610 --> 01:24:21.017
of the Quadroads of Erathis. The Gladekeepers of
the Birthheart stand behind the High Hierophant

01:24:21.017 --> 01:24:29.583
Ophera, while the dark-veiled maidens of the Raven
Queen gather, leaderless, as is their order. Pike

01:24:29.583 --> 01:24:34.047
stands at the edge of the council, trying to
listen in, before seeing you and rushing to your

01:24:34.047 --> 01:24:37.198
side. (panting) "Hi!"

01:24:37.198 --> 01:24:39.439
TRAVIS: Pike!

01:24:39.439 --> 01:24:45.289
MATT: She rushes in and gives a few quick hugs.
"Did it work? Did you do it?"

01:24:45.289 --> 01:24:49.002
TRAVIS: Yeah! (whispering) We got the stuff.

01:24:49.002 --> 01:24:51.370
LAURA: (whispering) We made them!

01:24:51.370 --> 01:24:58.183
MATT: "Good. Things are a bit tense." And as she
turns, you see now at the back of the council,

01:24:58.183 --> 01:25:04.755
towering over most others and without armed
support stands the dark-skinned, beautiful J'mon

01:25:04.755 --> 01:25:16.930
Sa Ord, their simple clothing swathed in a loose
hanging robe of gold and sky blue. J'mon's

01:25:16.930 --> 01:25:22.985
smoldering pupils shift in your direction, and
they give you a nod of respect. The discussions

01:25:22.985 --> 01:25:29.941
halt as you approach, recognition also falling
across the room. At which point, the Highbearer

01:25:29.941 --> 01:25:39.233
Vord turns to you saying, "Vox Machina, with a gift
of timing. Have you anything to aid in this crisis?"

01:25:39.233 --> 01:25:42.514
LAURA: Like, so much.

01:25:42.514 --> 01:25:50.651
MATT: "Then please, take the center of the
chambers. I believe everyone here could use some

01:25:50.651 --> 01:25:56.096
"form of good news." He steps back, and as the rest
of the guards empty, they open the central space

01:25:56.096 --> 01:25:58.463
of the chamber for you to approach.

01:25:58.463 --> 01:26:05.354
TALIESIN: Well, technically we've already been
observable, so there's very little that we can say

01:26:05.354 --> 01:26:06.810
that he doesn't already know.

01:26:06.810 --> 01:26:08.674
LAURA: He's listening right now.

01:26:08.674 --> 01:26:10.754
LIAM: How much do you know already?

01:26:10.754 --> 01:26:15.792
MATT: "We have only taken a bit from what your
companion here, Pike of the Everlight, has said.

01:26:15.792 --> 01:26:19.166
"You went off to a volcano?"

01:26:19.166 --> 01:26:22.034
TRAVIS: Scaldseat.

01:26:22.034 --> 01:26:24.579
MARISHA: And we defeated it!

01:26:24.579 --> 01:26:28.203
MATT: "You defeated a volcano?"

01:26:28.203 --> 01:26:29.602
TRAVIS: No.

01:26:29.602 --> 01:26:31.060
MARISHA: Kind of.

01:26:31.060 --> 01:26:39.264
LAURA: Look, I'm sure you've realized by this
point that Vecna has ascended to godhood.

01:26:39.264 --> 01:26:47.571
MATT: As he begins to speak, immediately the High
Hierophant Ophera steps forward. "Yes, the dreams

01:26:47.571 --> 01:26:55.611
"have spread. We've seen and spoken with the
clerics all across this land, and it seems that a

01:26:55.611 --> 01:27:01.765
"new force has shoved its way amongst the rest of
the pantheon, though apparently closer."

01:27:01.765 --> 01:27:09.894
LAURA: He's not reached his full power yet. The
only way it will happen is if he claims a great

01:27:09.894 --> 01:27:12.472
use of power.

01:27:12.472 --> 01:27:17.332
MARISHA: Yeah, performs a miracle. He needs
followers.

01:27:17.332 --> 01:27:21.941
LAURA: He's on his way here. The more followers he
has, the more power he has.

01:27:21.941 --> 01:27:26.804
MATT: At that, when you say, "he's on his way
here," you watch as Groon steps forward, arms

01:27:26.804 --> 01:27:32.826
still crossed. "How do you know he's coming?"

01:27:32.826 --> 01:27:39.624
MARISHA: (stammers) Just look outside.

01:27:39.624 --> 01:27:45.025
TRAVIS: Keyleth, hey, whoa. Take it down.

01:27:45.025 --> 01:27:49.910
SAM: We don't need the sass.

01:27:49.910 --> 01:27:52.444
MARISHA: But I'm not sassing!

01:27:52.444 --> 01:27:59.946
TRAVIS: With respect, there are those among us
that can tell where he is moving.

01:27:59.946 --> 01:28:01.387
LAURA: Yeah.

01:28:01.387 --> 01:28:03.555
LIAM: I am the paladin of the Raven Queen.

01:28:03.555 --> 01:28:11.981
MATT: At which point two of the maidens behind you
say in unison together, "That he is, and the

01:28:11.981 --> 01:28:17.614
"visions we've seen, as well. The pretender god.
His words, channeled through prayers, speak of a

01:28:17.614 --> 01:28:25.106
"new terror, a vile tyrant unchecked. Believe him.
His words are that of our lady." And both of them

01:28:25.106 --> 01:28:27.305
step back once more.

01:28:27.305 --> 01:28:29.244
MARISHA: Have you met them before?

01:28:29.244 --> 01:28:31.077
MATT: They said it in unison.

01:28:31.077 --> 01:28:35.568
MARISHA: Are you friends? Are you on the same
mailing list?

01:28:35.568 --> 01:28:39.771
LIAM: They all look similar.

01:28:39.771 --> 01:28:45.435
LAURA: So yeah, he's got this ability.

01:28:45.435 --> 01:28:52.930
LIAM: She has granted me knowledge of his
whereabouts, and he is coming fast.

01:28:52.930 --> 01:29:01.179
MATT: Vord now speaks up from behind. "Good, then
let us gather our resources. The esteemed J'mon Sa

01:29:01.179 --> 01:29:04.757
"Ord has agreed to lend aid and resources to our
defense."

01:29:04.757 --> 01:29:11.512
At which point, J'mon speaks up. "This threat
stretches beyond the borders of Issylra. The

01:29:11.512 --> 01:29:18.668
"clouds darken even our desert skies. If this
specter of the Age of Arcanum has indeed ascended,

01:29:18.668 --> 01:29:25.449
"as the clerics here are convinced, then it is a
threat that we of Ank'Harel cannot ignore."

01:29:25.449 --> 01:29:35.251
Vord then turns his head frustratingly to the east
and says, "And King Bertrand Dwendal has declined

01:29:35.295 --> 01:29:41.206
"aid, claiming that until this rumored scourge
arrives on Dwendalian soil, it is of no interest

01:29:41.206 --> 01:29:49.913
"to the crown of Wildemount. No resources can be
spared chasing whispers. We have sent out scouting

01:29:49.913 --> 01:29:54.946
"parties, however. As you've said, this threat
seems to be coming from the northwest, last you

01:29:54.946 --> 01:30:01.222
"came through. And wyvern riders are seeking the
location of this Thar Amphala."

01:30:01.222 --> 01:30:09.131
At which point, there's a flash of blue arcane
energy in the back of the room. Everyone turns;

01:30:09.131 --> 01:30:15.862
the guards have their weapons drawn out ready. And
you spin to see a familiar blonde-haired mage with

01:30:15.862 --> 01:30:17.132
braids on the side--

01:30:17.132 --> 01:30:21.353
(cheering)

01:30:21.353 --> 01:30:37.302
MATT: A bit out of breath, and in the same flash
behind, a golden-armored halfling of sun-kissed

01:30:37.302 --> 01:30:48.166
skin and long, golden, curling hair. Large weapon
dragging behind. Allura then, hand up in

01:30:48.166 --> 01:30:56.742
resignation, staff to the side. "We are merely
here to offer counsel and communication. We mean

01:30:56.742 --> 01:31:03.035
"no harm, nor to bring our arcane knowledge to your
quarters, and I apologize, but extenuating

01:31:03.035 --> 01:31:10.764
"circumstances require strange bedfellows, I think
you will agree. However, at the first sight of

01:31:10.764 --> 01:31:17.603
"threat upon Tal'Dorei, understand that we will
seek your assistance with haste, as well. Emon and

01:31:17.603 --> 01:31:24.420
"the council cannot survive another catastrophe, so
we are here to behest and ask only you're ready to

01:31:24.420 --> 01:31:28.877
"return depending on when or where this assault
strikes."

01:31:28.877 --> 01:31:37.149
There's a bit of muttering amongst the crowd and
some grumbling. Highbearer Vord nods. "We are in

01:31:37.149 --> 01:31:42.602
"need of aid and as many friends as we can gather.
You are welcome, Arcanist Vysoren."

01:31:42.602 --> 01:31:48.402
LAURA: Allura, does the sky look like this in
Emon?

01:31:48.402 --> 01:31:56.295
MATT: "It, in the past 12 hours or so, has
stretched across the Ozmit Sea and now seeks to

01:31:56.295 --> 01:32:04.833
"consume as far as the east coast of Tal'Dorei. If
this is what I believe it is, within the next

01:32:04.833 --> 01:32:11.597
"half-to-full day the entirety of Exandria will be
under the shaded sky of Vecna."

01:32:11.597 --> 01:32:22.571
SAM: Well, maybe the miracle thing is just the
change in weather, and we'll be okay.

01:32:22.571 --> 01:32:31.094
(laughter)

01:32:31.094 --> 01:32:34.707
SAM: Not all miracles have to be deadly.

01:32:34.707 --> 01:32:45.650
MATT: "Very well. Will you be there fighting with
our armies, in the front line?"

01:32:45.650 --> 01:32:53.133
TRAVIS: We will. I guess my only question is: do
we wait for him to come to us, or do we try to

01:32:53.133 --> 01:32:55.414
take the fight to him?

01:32:55.414 --> 01:33:02.223
MATT: "I do not wish to fight him where he expects
it. As we are a city that has prided itself on its

01:33:02.223 --> 01:33:10.709
"impenetrable defenses, I can guarantee you that
this entity has seemingly procured, or cleverly

01:33:10.709 --> 01:33:19.516
"divined, some way of breaching. I gather he would
expect less us bringing it to him. We hoped to

01:33:19.516 --> 01:33:24.355
"have information on the whereabouts of this city
directly. What else do we have?"

01:33:24.355 --> 01:33:28.225
LAURA: We have the knowledge that we can't take
him by surprise.

01:33:28.225 --> 01:33:31.825
MATT: "What do you mean?"

01:33:31.825 --> 01:33:33.680
LAURA: He sees everything.

01:33:33.680 --> 01:33:35.335
TALIESIN: He hears everything.

01:33:35.335 --> 01:33:39.235
TRAVIS: Yeah, he's been spying on us for quite
some time now, little shit.

01:33:39.235 --> 01:33:42.304
MARISHA: I wouldn't be surprised if there is a spy
in this room.

01:33:42.304 --> 01:33:45.406
TALIESIN: Or at least an open ear.

01:33:45.406 --> 01:33:53.496
MARISHA: You have citizens of your city that are
starting to paint his symbol on their doors out of

01:33:53.496 --> 01:34:03.263
fear. This is the last thing you want in the
middle of this crisis. All time spent with any

01:34:03.263 --> 01:34:11.412
volunteer hands need to be from any spare clerics
who can help calm the minds of the afraid.

01:34:11.412 --> 01:34:17.300
MATT: He looks out amongst the rest of the crowd
that has gathered here in the center inner

01:34:17.300 --> 01:34:28.545
sanctum. "Her words speak true. If he's indeed
seeking to undermine the worship of this city, and

01:34:28.545 --> 01:34:39.715
"as such break the defenses of our great creators,
then we need whatever strength your temples have

01:34:39.715 --> 01:34:45.195
"here, calming the people of Vasselheim and beyond.
If you think he sees all--"

01:34:45.195 --> 01:34:49.292
TALIESIN: I think he sees this city as a ripe
audience.

01:34:49.292 --> 01:35:07.578
MATT: At this point, you watch as Vord steps
forward, fiddling with one finger. "Long ago, this

01:35:07.578 --> 01:35:17.870
"grand temple nearly fell to the prying minds of
terrible mages. This here," and he pulls a ring

01:35:17.870 --> 01:35:26.842
from his finger, "is called the Band of Shrouds, a
powerful implement of the Highbearer to shunt

01:35:26.842 --> 01:35:40.287
"these prying magics aside. I lend it to you for
the coming struggle." And he passes it over to

01:35:40.287 --> 01:35:46.827
Vex'ahlia.

01:35:46.827 --> 01:35:49.726
LAURA: Yes!

01:35:49.726 --> 01:35:57.982
MATT: "Kept close enough to the one who wears this
ring, I doubt even his newly born eyes could

01:35:57.982 --> 01:36:09.206
"pierce it. However, it can only affect those
nearby, so if you are to strike, perhaps it's best

01:36:09.206 --> 01:36:12.517
"you do so away from his vision, and we distract."

01:36:12.517 --> 01:36:16.936
LAURA: So he can't hear us right now?

01:36:16.936 --> 01:36:21.989
MATT: Everyone in the room takes a few steps
closer to you.

01:36:21.989 --> 01:36:25.271
(laughter)

01:36:25.271 --> 01:36:30.560
MATT: "Within this chamber, it seems so, yes."

01:36:30.560 --> 01:36:34.319
LAURA: (sighs) It feels so good!

01:36:34.319 --> 01:36:38.982
LIAM: I think that would look better on your
middle finger, darling.

01:36:38.982 --> 01:36:43.013
LAURA: Oh, good call.

01:36:43.013 --> 01:36:49.181
MATT: At which point the doors in the back of the
chamber burst open once more, and you watch as two

01:36:49.181 --> 01:36:57.008
armored figures come rushing up out of breath.
(panting) You see as these two wyvern riders,

01:36:57.008 --> 01:37:03.665
recognizing their armor with the horns and the
large dragon-like build of their armor and

01:37:03.665 --> 01:37:10.017
headpiece, looking damaged and splashed with
crimson, come charging in. One of them, the helmet

01:37:10.017 --> 01:37:16.626
is removed and you see a young man shouting
through his wounded breaths. "Highbearer! Rider

01:37:16.626 --> 01:37:26.306
"Ephatus, with Rider Marley, returning from beyond
Moldire and the Tordusk pass. We found the Dark City."

01:37:26.306 --> 01:37:30.796
Everyone immediately begins to mutter beneath
their breath. The voices begin to rise as the

01:37:30.796 --> 01:37:37.341
Highbearer puts his hand out to hush them. "It
lies within a valley a few miles into the Zenwick

01:37:37.341 --> 01:37:43.552
"Mountains. Our team attempted to infiltrate, but
an unseeable barrier protects the city grounds

01:37:43.552 --> 01:37:49.456
"from all sides. We found ourselves overrun by
errant magics and winged beasts of shadow and

01:37:49.456 --> 01:37:54.360
"hunger. Only Marley and myself survived. We were
only a scouting regiment!"

01:37:54.360 --> 01:38:03.802
At which point, the High Hierophant steps forward.
"Zenwick, of all places. Curious indeed."

01:38:03.802 --> 01:38:13.481
The Highbearer turns again. "Very well, if this is
true, we must mobilize our forces very quickly."

01:38:13.481 --> 01:38:20.480
Groon steps forward once more. "We can push our
ground troops along the Glasswalk Road, towards

01:38:20.480 --> 01:38:22.232
"the range."

01:38:22.232 --> 01:38:29.981
Allura steps forward to join the conversation. "If
we can choose some elite select numbers for an

01:38:29.981 --> 01:38:32.723
"onsite assault, I can transport them."

01:38:32.723 --> 01:38:39.995
At which point the Curator Curtis steps in.
"You'll do nothing of the kind! It is arcane

01:38:39.995 --> 01:38:45.675
"perversions that enabled this madman, and we will
&lt;i&gt;not&lt;/i&gt; allow--"

01:38:45.675 --> 01:38:51.668
Ophera steps forward, putting her hand in front of
his face now, saying, "We have druids who are

01:38:51.668 --> 01:38:57.711
"familiar with the woods surrounding the base of
the Zenwick Mountains. We could transport you to

01:38:57.711 --> 01:39:01.130
"those trees, a number of you, for an initial
assault while the rest of our ground forces

01:39:01.130 --> 01:39:03.529
"assemble northward."

01:39:03.529 --> 01:39:13.873
At which point, the wounded rider speaks up,
loudly. "I am not done! My apologies. Only Marley

01:39:13.873 --> 01:39:20.383
"and myself survived with one of our wyverns. As we
fled over the nearest mountaintop as fast as we

01:39:20.383 --> 01:39:22.727
"could, Marley saw--"

01:39:22.727 --> 01:39:28.668
And the other one takes her helmet off, and you
can see caked with blood, one eye swollen shut and

01:39:28.668 --> 01:39:40.101
a giant wound across the face. "I saw the city
move, part of it. It moved, I swear it. I heard a

01:39:40.101 --> 01:39:51.899
"rumble over the winds, looked past and back over
our shoulders, and I saw the city begin to rise."

01:39:51.899 --> 01:39:58.623
Silence takes the room. I would like any of you
with a fair amount of history to make a history check.

01:39:58.623 --> 01:40:04.371
TALIESIN: What's a fair amount?

01:40:04.371 --> 01:40:08.073
MATT: If you feel confident in your ability to
understand history. I would say putting it this

01:40:08.073 --> 01:40:11.360
way, those who have researched the lands that
would probably be Percival and Scanlan.

01:40:11.360 --> 01:40:17.899
TALIESIN: Okay.

01:40:17.899 --> 01:40:22.811
SAM: 27!

01:40:22.811 --> 01:40:24.052
TALIESIN: 21.

01:40:24.052 --> 01:40:35.291
MATT: 27? Okay! I'll make part of this a whisper.

01:40:35.291 --> 01:40:38.446
LAURA: Wait, you'll make what? I didn't hear it!

01:40:38.446 --> 01:40:39.862
SAM: A &lt;i&gt;live&lt;/i&gt; whisper.

01:40:39.862 --> 01:40:46.240
MATT: There are two places in the Zenwick
Mountains that would be of any interest, or

01:40:46.240 --> 01:40:54.025
historical lore-based elements. There is the
Crypts of Thomara: it's a subterranean vault city,

01:40:54.025 --> 01:41:02.057
built around a precious metal vein cluster by the
xenophobic dwarven Thomara clan in the early years

01:41:02.057 --> 01:41:08.708
of the Age of Arcana. It's said a terrible madness
fed into their greed, leading to eventual

01:41:08.708 --> 01:41:15.396
cannibalism and collapse of the society thousands
of years ago. It's now considered cursed and is

01:41:15.396 --> 01:41:23.936
largely avoided. The other location is known as
the Silted Veil, a small, cold valley within the

01:41:23.936 --> 01:41:29.014
mountains that is comprised of ice-dusted, mineral-rich
mud that was once rumored to carry natural

01:41:29.014 --> 01:41:33.815
healing properties when applied to wounds and
restorative elements to aged skin. However, a

01:41:33.815 --> 01:41:38.779
large variety of dangerous creatures also
discovered these features over time and moved into

01:41:38.779 --> 01:41:45.657
the valley, taking over and establishing a new
violent ecosystem based around the soothing muck.

01:41:45.657 --> 01:41:53.949
Scanlan.

01:41:53.949 --> 01:41:56.064
AUDIENCE MEMBER: Hey guys, so those t-shirts--

01:41:56.064 --> 01:42:00.428
(laughter)

01:42:00.428 --> 01:42:07.575
LAURA: Very true. There is Critical Role live Vox
Machina t-shirts.

01:42:07.575 --> 01:42:12.464
MARISHA: Okay so the Crypts of (stumbles over
words) Tholmeer? Crypts of Tholmayer and the

01:42:12.464 --> 01:42:13.750
Silted Veil.

01:42:13.750 --> 01:42:18.882
LAURA: Silted Veil and the Crypts of Tholmura?

01:42:18.882 --> 01:42:22.954
MARISHA: Yeah, which are the two places in the
Zenwick Mountains?

01:42:22.954 --> 01:42:26.391
LAURA: And one is icy valley, the other one is,
what, zombie dwarves?

01:42:26.391 --> 01:42:27.493
MARISHA: Yeah.

01:42:27.493 --> 01:42:30.553
TALIESIN: Cannibal zombie dwarves.

01:42:30.553 --> 01:42:35.216
MARISHA: Angry icy terrain or cannibal zombie
dwarves.

01:42:35.216 --> 01:42:36.034
LAURA: Okay.

01:42:36.034 --> 01:42:45.160
MATT: At this information, Vord nods. "Well, all
forces on high for impending attack here, wyvern

01:42:45.160 --> 01:42:50.745
"riders and air units, we need eyes on the Tordusk
Pass, in case the city is indeed moving as they

01:42:50.745 --> 01:42:57.047
"say. The High Hierophant will aid in transporting
advanced scouts to the base of the Zenwicks. We

01:42:57.047 --> 01:43:02.580
"would wish you be part of this if you are willing
and able. Gathering information and seeking

01:43:02.580 --> 01:43:11.337
"weakness to exploit are the key. Vox Machina, you
are our focused stealth strike force into Thar

01:43:11.337 --> 01:43:13.192
"Amphala."

01:43:13.192 --> 01:43:16.878
LAURA: Yeah! We're &lt;i&gt;mostly&lt;/i&gt; really good at that.

01:43:16.878 --> 01:43:26.431
MATT: "If you indeed carry the boons that your
lady Pike has mentioned, then we need to keep

01:43:26.431 --> 01:43:38.487
Vecna and his force occupied to grant you entry.
And we can do that. I certainly hope with the

01:43:38.487 --> 01:43:43.940
strength of our numbers that there is no way that
he can see them coming.

01:43:43.940 --> 01:43:55.764
From the distant end of the central chamber here,
a familiar voice echoes throughout the hallway.

01:43:55.764 --> 01:44:07.815
"Oh, but I do, wyrm groveler."

01:44:07.815 --> 01:44:13.668
SAM: But the ring, man! We just got the ring!

01:44:13.668 --> 01:44:15.891
MATT: You haven't attuned to it yet.

01:44:15.891 --> 01:44:18.348
LAURA: Fuck!

01:44:18.348 --> 01:44:20.532
MATT: And with that, we're going to go ahead and
take our break.

01:44:20.532 --> 01:44:28.116
(cheering)

01:44:28.116 --> 01:44:30.125
LAURA: Come on!

01:44:30.125 --> 01:44:32.578
MARISHA: What all did we say?

01:44:32.578 --> 01:44:35.454
TALIESIN: What &lt;i&gt;didn't&lt;/i&gt; we say?

01:44:35.454 --> 01:44:38.833
LAURA: Shit!

01:44:38.833 --> 01:44:40.960
LIAM: What a piece of shit!

01:44:40.960 --> 01:44:45.651
MATT: We'll take our break here. We'll return at
that moment here in a number of minutes.

01:44:45.651 --> 01:44:48.183
SAM: Ten minutes? 15 minutes? What are we doing?

01:44:48.183 --> 01:44:52.040
MATT: You'll know when the lights start going.
We'll have people out there who'll let you know.

01:44:52.040 --> 01:44:56.891
It won't be too terribly long, we need to get a
bathroom break and stuff. Anyway, be back here in

01:44:56.891 --> 01:45:01.678
a little bit, guys, we'll see you for the next
portion of our journey this evening.

01:45:01.678 --> 02:07:01.119
[break]

02:07:01.153 --> 02:07:06.574
LAURA: Fucked up because it's Trinket. It's a
Trinket cape. Yeah, but thank you. It's gorgeous.

02:07:06.574 --> 02:07:08.807
TRAVIS: Really? Right now?

02:07:08.807 --> 02:07:11.798
MARISHA: I'm rolling with someone's lucky die that
I got delivered.

02:07:11.798 --> 02:07:18.225
AUDIENCE MEMBER: Gets a little hot!

02:07:18.225 --> 02:07:20.419
LAURA: Yeah, it's warm. I'm already very warm.

02:07:20.419 --> 02:07:22.587
TALIESIN: It's a little cold up here. That's
okay.

02:07:22.587 --> 02:07:24.524
AUDIENCE MEMBER: We love you guys!

02:07:24.524 --> 02:07:26.837
TALIESIN: There they are.

02:07:26.837 --> 02:07:31.306
(laughter)

02:07:31.306 --> 02:07:57.369
TALIESIN: Oh my god.

