SAM: We're best buds!

02:44:29.925 --> 02:44:36.404
LIAM: Best buds! Best buds, met at Big Apple Anime
Fest in New York City all those years ago.

02:44:36.404 --> 02:44:40.189
AUDIENCE: Aww.

02:44:40.189 --> 02:44:49.397
SAM: All right, I'll take two.

02:44:49.397 --> 02:44:50.733
LAURA: Yeah. Okay.

02:44:50.733 --> 02:44:52.736
SAM: In Marquesian I say, thank you, J'mon Sa Ord.

02:44:52.736 --> 02:44:55.753
MATT: "Be pleased."

02:44:55.753 --> 02:44:59.307
LAURA: We are. Very.

02:44:59.307 --> 02:45:12.393
SAM: Also, if you don't like the Meat Man, I can
make him go away.

02:45:12.393 --> 02:45:20.642
MATT: "Their business has not encroached upon the
order that we maintain. Yet."

02:45:20.642 --> 02:45:23.460
(laughter)

02:45:23.460 --> 02:45:25.601
MATT: "You'd know if it did."

02:45:25.601 --> 02:45:27.899
LIAM: (whispers) They know!

02:45:27.899 --> 02:45:38.619
MATT: The smoldering pupils that they contain
within their darkened eyes stare back at you with

02:45:38.619 --> 02:45:40.629
a curling smile.

02:45:40.629 --> 02:45:46.898
SAM: Thank you. Let's go. We've got to get through
this druidy thing, right?

02:45:46.898 --> 02:45:53.421
MATT: Ophera backs up and, putting her staff to one
side, makes a large oval shape with her fingers as

02:45:53.421 --> 02:45:57.807
she mutters beneath her breath. You watch as one
of the heavy, thick trunks of the nearest tree

02:45:57.807 --> 02:46:02.413
begins to tear and crack and pull inward. And
there you see in a similar fashion to Keyleth's

02:46:02.413 --> 02:46:09.574
casting, though a little more visceral, an opening
reveals itself and a doorway is opened, and she

02:46:09.574 --> 02:46:11.405
goes, "Quick! Now!"

02:46:11.405 --> 02:46:14.237
MARISHA: I like your technique!

02:46:14.237 --> 02:46:22.547
MATT: You all rush through, one after another,
flanked at the end by J'mon. And as you all

02:46:22.547 --> 02:46:29.620
approach the opposite side of this portal, you
emerge in a somewhat crowded forest of pine trees.

02:46:29.620 --> 02:46:37.646
Immediately, the northern air is colder, and you
see drifting bits of snowfall softly coming

02:46:37.646 --> 02:46:42.570
through bits of the tree line above you. You turn
around just in time to see the doorway close, and

02:46:42.570 --> 02:46:49.402
in the distance you see other doorways opening
around you in different trees, and you watch as

02:46:49.402 --> 02:46:55.340
dozens upon dozens of wyvern riders and armored
soldiers begin to emerge, one cluster after the next.

02:46:55.340 --> 02:46:57.580
MARISHA: Fucking druids are badass!

02:46:57.580 --> 02:47:03.958
TALIESIN: Let's do this.

02:47:03.958 --> 02:47:14.454
MATT: You glance up and can briefly see the top
northern crest of where the Zenwick Mountain pass

02:47:14.454 --> 02:47:21.189
is. Just past the canopy of the forest you're in,
because you were sent to the very slim base of the

02:47:21.189 --> 02:47:27.499
Zenwick Mountains. You're within a forest. What do
you want to do?

02:47:27.499 --> 02:47:30.039
LIAM: What does my Vec-dar tell me?

02:47:30.039 --> 02:47:35.708
MATT: Interestingly enough, southeast of where you
are.

02:47:35.708 --> 02:47:37.155
LIAM: Shit.

02:47:37.155 --> 02:47:39.142
LAURA: How close?

02:47:39.142 --> 02:47:44.708
MATT: I'd say it's probably close to four miles
from where you are.

02:47:44.708 --> 02:47:52.152
LAURA: Oh shit.

02:47:52.152 --> 02:47:55.816
MATT: And slowly moving away.

02:47:55.816 --> 02:48:00.457
LIAM: We guessed wrong?

02:48:00.457 --> 02:48:02.030
MARISHA: Four miles.

02:48:02.030 --> 02:48:05.484
TALIESIN: Did we guess wrong?

02:48:05.484 --> 02:48:09.102
LIAM: Well, we don't know where this shit is that
we're looking for.

02:48:09.102 --> 02:48:10.770
SAM: Do we know where these things are?

02:48:10.770 --> 02:48:14.274
MATT: They're both northwest of where you are, in
the mountain range.

02:48:14.274 --> 02:48:15.890
MARISHA: He's passed them.

02:48:15.890 --> 02:48:16.871
LIAM: Passed over.

02:48:16.871 --> 02:48:18.341
MATT: He's passed over, it seems.

02:48:18.341 --> 02:48:19.348
LIAM: Fuck.

02:48:19.348 --> 02:48:22.635
SAM: What do we do?

02:48:22.635 --> 02:48:30.320
MARISHA: If we get a little bit closer, I can do a
Commune with Nature spell and try and figure out

02:48:30.320 --> 02:48:32.934
some stuff. It's all I've got. I can scry!

02:48:32.934 --> 02:48:39.057
LAURA: I mean, if he's already passed by the
crypts, is there any reason to go there? I don't

02:48:39.057 --> 02:48:40.163
understand.

02:48:40.163 --> 02:48:42.950
TRAVIS: What direction is Vasselheim from us now?

02:48:42.950 --> 02:48:44.349
MATT: Southeast.

02:48:44.349 --> 02:48:45.798
MARISHA: The way they're heading.

02:48:45.798 --> 02:48:51.105
TRAVIS: Anybody else think we should fucking hop
on a big-ass brass dragon and try and catch him

02:48:51.105 --> 02:49:00.906
before he gets there? What are we going to do
here? There's nothing to do here!

02:49:00.906 --> 02:49:02.845
LAURA: You want us to go fight Vecna right now?

02:49:02.845 --> 02:49:06.513
TRAVIS: Either that, or he goes and sacks the city
and we're like, "What does this tree tell me about

02:49:06.513 --> 02:49:07.969
"this area?"

02:49:07.969 --> 02:49:17.957
(laughter)

02:49:17.957 --> 02:49:21.949
LIAM: Quickly, please, someone come up with an argument
that counteracts that.

02:49:21.949 --> 02:49:24.769
TALIESIN: We should scry on the dwarven city if we
can, really quickly.

02:49:24.769 --> 02:49:26.969
SAM: How? We don't know much about it.

02:49:26.969 --> 02:49:28.615
TALIESIN: Do we know enough to scry?

02:49:28.615 --> 02:49:34.900
MARISHA: I can scry on Lady Briarwood.

02:49:34.900 --> 02:49:38.383
LAURA: Do it. Do it right now.

02:49:38.383 --> 02:49:40.779
TALIESIN and MARISHA: Ooh!

02:49:40.779 --> 02:49:43.471
MARISHA: Yeah, I bet she's with him.

02:49:43.471 --> 02:49:45.542
TALIESIN: Or she's not.

02:49:45.542 --> 02:49:48.153
LIAM: We'll learn something.

02:49:48.153 --> 02:49:51.154
LAURA: Are you zoning in on the city, or are you
zoning in on Vecna?

02:49:51.154 --> 02:49:55.593
TALIESIN: We know where Vecna is. We just need to
see where Lady Briarwood is.

02:49:55.593 --> 02:49:57.740
MARISHA: All right, scrying on Briarwood. Oh, she
rolls.

02:49:57.740 --> 02:50:00.031
MATT: She rolls. To make a saving roll. Spell DC
is?

02:50:00.031 --> 02:50:01.858
MARISHA: 21!

02:50:01.858 --> 02:50:04.384
MATT: And that is a 22.

02:50:04.384 --> 02:50:08.529
(groaning)

02:50:08.529 --> 02:50:13.959
MATT: Sorry. As you try and focus, the incantation
completes and as your vision begins to extend it

02:50:13.959 --> 02:50:18.151
is blocked by darkness and sent back into your
form. And you realize the scry has failed, the

02:50:18.151 --> 02:50:19.514
will is too strong.

02:50:19.514 --> 02:50:22.479
LAURA: Can you scry on that death knight guy that
was next to her?

02:50:22.479 --> 02:50:27.341
MARISHA: Is he still with her, though?

02:50:27.341 --> 02:50:32.726
LAURA: We didn't kill him. We did not kill him. We
did not hit him! We did not!

02:50:32.726 --> 02:50:36.763
(laughter)

02:50:36.763 --> 02:50:45.750
MARISHA: Oh, hi Vex. All right. I'll scry on
undead douchey.

02:50:45.750 --> 02:50:55.483
MATT: As your vision extends from you, it races
through the darkness. You see dark clouds ahead.

02:50:55.483 --> 02:51:03.606
As it fires down, you look instantly within the
streets of Thar Amphala. You see the cobblestone

02:51:03.606 --> 02:51:11.679
roads now cracked and broken, you see buildings
appear to have sustained structural damage. You

02:51:11.679 --> 02:51:16.631
see roofs are partially collapsed. And walking
down the street, strolling with a number of undead

02:51:16.631 --> 02:51:21.897
soldiers at its back, the black knight you battled
before. As it struts through you watch as the

02:51:21.897 --> 02:51:32.831
towers and buildings (rumbling) shake. And shake
again. And your vision returns.

02:51:32.831 --> 02:51:34.581
TALIESIN: Oh shit.

02:51:34.581 --> 02:51:42.501
MARISHA: It was shaking-- Oh, is it on the back of
some giant turtle or something?

02:51:42.501 --> 02:51:45.488
(laughter)

02:51:45.488 --> 02:51:48.647
TALIESIN: We should stop that from happening.

02:51:48.647 --> 02:51:52.362
TRAVIS: Yeah, we're super lucky and it's just a
turtle.

02:51:52.362 --> 02:52:00.735
(laughter)

02:52:00.735 --> 02:52:03.222
TRAVIS: How lucky for us!

02:52:03.222 --> 02:52:05.258
MARISHA: It'd be so cute.

02:52:05.258 --> 02:52:12.148
MATT: "Then there is no time to waste." You watch
as J'mon Sa Ord's form shifts and giant brass

02:52:12.148 --> 02:52:22.303
wings extend in a flash of reddish-orange energy.
The nearby trees bend and break at the sheer force

02:52:22.303 --> 02:52:29.334
of the dragon's magnitude, their form expanding to
fill the recent vicinity of the forest, and with a

02:52:29.334 --> 02:52:35.897
large guttural roar, you see before you the brass
dragon.

02:52:35.897 --> 02:52:39.330
SAM: Shotgun!

02:52:39.330 --> 02:52:45.373
LAURA: Hey, Keyleth? While we're flying through
the air, is it possible for you to give us a nice

02:52:45.373 --> 02:52:47.754
inspiring speech?

02:52:47.754 --> 02:52:50.554
MARISHA: Oh! (giggles)

02:52:50.554 --> 02:52:54.315
TRAVIS: (laughs)

02:52:54.315 --> 02:53:01.450
LIAM: It's all right. It's just our small group
here. No one's watching. You know us.

02:53:01.450 --> 02:53:11.913
MARISHA: Yeah. Man, inspiring speech. So we're on
a brass dragon?

02:53:11.913 --> 02:53:18.412
MATT: You can do it while you're all climbing on
the back. They're waiting patiently for you all to

02:53:18.412 --> 02:53:21.364
jump onto the back of the dragon form.

02:53:21.364 --> 02:53:27.973
SAM: If you need a second to think about it, it's
okay. We can start off first and then come back to you.

02:53:27.973 --> 02:53:29.775
MARISHA: Wait, what?

02:53:29.775 --> 02:53:32.080
SAM: Do you need a second to compose yourself?

02:53:32.080 --> 02:53:35.677
MARISHA: You know, Scanlan.

02:53:35.677 --> 02:53:42.734
(cheering)

02:53:42.734 --> 02:53:49.951
MARISHA: It's funny you should mention that,
because I do need a second. I have to think about

02:53:49.951 --> 02:53:56.567
my words deeply and a long time, and even still,
they come out wrong, and you're so witty and

02:53:56.567 --> 02:54:01.987
quick! And you can come up with things like
speeches and songs on the fly in front of

02:54:01.987 --> 02:54:12.281
thousands of people way quicker than I can. It is
not my strength, but I do know my strength, and I

02:54:12.281 --> 02:54:27.092
know each of your strengths. But not as well of
each of you know your strengths as well as you do.

02:54:27.092 --> 02:54:33.832
SAM: Sing it, sister.

02:54:33.832 --> 02:54:40.661
MARISHA: What I'm saying is, you should believe in
yourselves the way that I believe in you, Scanlan.

02:54:40.661 --> 02:54:52.091
And the way that you believe in everyone else,
Scanlan! Because you're all strong and unique. And

02:54:52.091 --> 02:54:53.826
we're probably going to die.

02:54:53.826 --> 02:54:58.865
(laughter)

02:54:58.865 --> 02:55:04.036
MARISHA: (stammers) Okay, let's fly! Ahoy!

02:55:04.036 --> 02:55:27.292
MATT: With a slow, metallic, crinkling sound of
brass dragon scales curling, the large head of

02:55:27.292 --> 02:55:34.196
J'mon Sa Ord's dragon form spins around to look
you dead in the face, Keyleth. The same dark eyes

02:55:34.196 --> 02:55:39.103
with the smoldering, burning cores for pupils, the
mouth opens and you can smell immediately the

02:55:39.103 --> 02:55:46.602
breath that has a very earthy, singed, burnt-wood
scent to it.

02:55:46.602 --> 02:55:50.638
MARISHA: Ooh, cedar!

02:55:50.638 --> 02:56:00.925
MATT: And the voice goes forth. "Very good,
Keyleth. I found that quite inspiring."

02:56:00.925 --> 02:56:12.745
(cheering)

02:56:12.745 --> 02:56:16.294
MATT: And with that, you guys can all take your 18
temporary hit points.

02:56:16.294 --> 02:56:18.587
TRAVIS: How much is it?

02:56:18.587 --> 02:56:20.695
TALIESIN: 18 temporary hit points?

02:56:20.695 --> 02:56:30.454
MATT: And with that note, with one large push of
their strong dragon wings, J'mon Sa Ord raises

02:56:30.454 --> 02:56:35.249
beyond the treeline up into the sky above, where
you can see the clusters of wyvern riders have now

02:56:35.249 --> 02:56:42.957
also gathered to survey the territory. The first
thing you notice, the southward wall, the tall,

02:56:42.957 --> 02:56:48.395
rocky landscape surrounding the fields of ice,
dust, and grasses that fill this pass, you can see

02:56:48.395 --> 02:56:55.251
the mountain range seems to have suffered an
immense amount of damage. A gargantuan fresh

02:56:55.251 --> 02:57:00.534
rockslide nearly a mile wide, now resting at the
base of the northern mountain, you can see

02:57:00.534 --> 02:57:04.337
swallowing and burying some of the forest land.

02:57:04.337 --> 02:57:16.711
And as you glance southward into the Tordusk Pass,
you can see mammoth holes in the ground, large

02:57:16.711 --> 02:57:23.989
craters of broken dirt and rock forced into dunes
of mud and shale surrounding their outsides. The

02:57:23.989 --> 02:57:31.982
scars, pockmarks 200 feet across, carved into the
terrain. I'd like everyone to make an intelligence

02:57:31.982 --> 02:57:34.085
check, please.

02:57:34.085 --> 02:57:38.480
LAURA: We're making a what, an intelligence
check?

02:57:38.480 --> 02:57:40.739
MARISHA: Can I do a nature check?

02:57:40.739 --> 02:57:41.718
MATT: Sure.

02:57:41.718 --> 02:57:42.641
MARISHA: Yeah?

02:57:42.641 --> 02:58:01.496
(cheering)

02:58:01.496 --> 02:58:03.123
MATT: Vex'ahlia?

02:58:03.179 --> 02:58:04.711
LAURA: Is this an intelligence?

02:58:04.711 --> 02:58:06.177
MATT: Yes. This is your intelligence modifier.

02:58:06.177 --> 02:58:07.076
LAURA: 21.

02:58:07.076 --> 02:58:08.777
MATT: 21, good. Vax?

02:58:08.777 --> 02:58:11.166
LIAM: Oh, man. Eight.

02:58:11.166 --> 02:58:13.355
MATT: Keyleth?

02:58:13.355 --> 02:58:15.471
MARISHA: I am doing a nature check.

02:58:15.471 --> 02:58:16.688
MATT: Right, to find out?

02:58:16.688 --> 02:58:24.045
MARISHA: If it looks like a path has been bore
through in a straight line, like it looks like

02:58:24.045 --> 02:58:25.710
it's going through. 24.

02:58:25.710 --> 02:58:31.202
MATT: 24? What you can tell from a nature check is
that these are not natural formations in the

02:58:31.202 --> 02:58:39.058
ground. These are blunt trauma to the ground that
has caused these large craters.

02:58:39.058 --> 02:58:42.840
LAURA: Does it look like a walking path? A very
large walking path?

02:58:42.840 --> 02:58:44.493
MATT: Percival?

02:58:44.493 --> 02:58:46.232
TALIESIN: Natural 20, for 25.

02:58:46.232 --> 02:58:50.330
MATT: Scanlan?

02:58:50.330 --> 02:58:51.454
SAM: 19 total.

02:58:51.454 --> 02:58:57.704
MATT: Okay. Percival. And Keyleth. And Perc'ahlia.
Not you Grog, sorry.

02:58:57.704 --> 02:59:00.725
TRAVIS: Holes!

02:59:00.725 --> 02:59:13.065
MATT: You do notice, upon immediate view, that
these large holes are patterned, staggered about

02:59:13.065 --> 02:59:24.672
every 350-400 feet. And they do almost present the
gait of a walking creature.

02:59:24.672 --> 02:59:27.637
MARISHA: (anguished sounds)

02:59:27.637 --> 02:59:30.045
TRAVIS: Hey! You got that big fucking turtle you
wanted!

02:59:30.045 --> 02:59:34.776
MARISHA: It is a giant turtle!

02:59:34.776 --> 02:59:41.415
LIAM: The final miniature is just Matt.

02:59:41.415 --> 02:59:48.221
MATT: "It has been foreseen!" I've been working on
my costume.

02:59:48.221 --> 02:59:53.325
LAURA: Do we see anything in the air, any of those
shadow creatures? Or is it just our wyvern

02:59:53.325 --> 02:59:54.121
riders?

02:59:54.121 --> 02:59:58.115
MATT: Make a perception check.

02:59:58.115 --> 02:59:59.588
LAURA: Natural 20!

02:59:59.588 --> 03:00:07.002
MATT: Okay. As you lift up to survey more
territory, you manage to get a brief view over the

03:00:07.002 --> 03:00:14.945
edge of that mountain range. You do not see any of
the gloomstalkers that you had previously faced

03:00:14.945 --> 03:00:19.768
near Thar Amphala. In the vicinity, there is only
the wyvern riders and a few errant birds that

03:00:19.768 --> 03:00:24.925
normally take to the skies that are keeping a wide
berth from your sudden emerging army that has

03:00:24.925 --> 03:00:30.138
joined you in the skies. You glance over this
mountain range, and you look about. About two,

03:00:30.138 --> 03:00:35.295
three miles northward, you can see the same path
of destruction has torn through these mountain

03:00:35.295 --> 03:00:43.049
ranges in a sinkhole, hundreds and hundreds of
feet across that disappears into darkness.

03:00:43.049 --> 03:00:50.753
LAURA: Is the sinkhole in the direction of the
city that's moving right now?

03:00:50.753 --> 03:00:53.809
MATT: No, it's in the direction you guys were
planning to travel.

03:00:53.809 --> 03:00:57.164
SAM: Oh. Maybe that's where they ripped the thing
out.

03:00:57.164 --> 03:01:02.958
TALIESIN: It's where it came out. How big are
these footprints, approximately?

03:01:02.958 --> 03:01:11.519
LAURA: (shouting) That's the fucking titan! It's
the titan full of dwarf bodies! I just realized that!

03:01:11.519 --> 03:01:14.255
(laughter)

03:01:14.255 --> 03:01:19.248
MARISHA: It totally fucking is, yeah. Yeah.

03:01:19.248 --> 03:01:22.734
LIAM: And his name is Larkin.

03:01:22.734 --> 03:01:28.166
(laughter)

03:01:28.166 --> 03:01:36.429
LAURA: Shit! I thought it was just a really big
giant, and then I remembered it was a titan.

03:01:36.457 --> 03:01:43.917
MATT: Yes, each one of these craters is roughly
150 or so feet across.

03:01:43.917 --> 03:01:47.705
SAM: Oh, his feet are a hundred feet across?!

03:01:47.705 --> 03:01:49.458
MATT: 150 to 200 feet across, yeah.

03:01:49.458 --> 03:01:53.898
TALIESIN: Keyleth, how big would a creature be if
it had footprints approximately 150 to 200 feet

03:01:53.898 --> 03:01:54.840
across?

03:01:54.840 --> 03:01:59.599
SAM: At least a hundred feet big!

03:01:59.599 --> 03:02:01.161
MARISHA: Probably bigger?

03:02:01.161 --> 03:02:03.537
SAM: Maybe even bigger!

03:02:03.537 --> 03:02:07.667
MARISHA: Can I do a nature check to find out how
fucking big this guy is?

03:02:07.667 --> 03:02:09.079
MATT: Sure.

03:02:09.079 --> 03:02:17.451
MARISHA: Yeah! Let's do this lucky one. That's not
too bad. 28.

03:02:17.451 --> 03:02:21.123
MATT: Based on your experience with various
creatures that leave large tracks you've dealt

03:02:21.123 --> 03:02:30.100
with or hunted in your history with the Ashari,
it's &lt;i&gt;big&lt;/i&gt;. The legs generally are pretty thick

03:02:30.100 --> 03:02:37.748
for a creature of immense size because it has to
support all that weight, but if each footfall,

03:02:37.748 --> 03:02:44.759
crater here is about 150, 200 feet wide, you can
surmise the creature is hundreds of feet tall.

03:02:44.759 --> 03:02:46.824
TRAVIS: At least six times.

03:02:46.824 --> 03:02:53.339
LAURA: At least 600 feet tall. What did you say?

03:02:53.339 --> 03:02:56.098
LIAM: I said we're going to have to Shadow of
Colossus this shit.

03:02:56.098 --> 03:02:58.734
LAURA: How are we going to fucking fight something
that's 600 feet tall?

03:02:58.734 --> 03:03:01.600
TRAVIS: If it bleeds, we-- we're going to die.

03:03:01.600 --> 03:03:12.309
(laughter)

03:03:12.309 --> 03:03:19.653
MARISHA: Hang on, though. Caverns. Undead caverns
of dwarves inside the titan.

03:03:19.682 --> 03:03:23.578
LIAM: Yeah, maybe we crawl up its butthole and
kill the things inside.

03:03:23.578 --> 03:03:26.623
MARISHA: Yeah, maybe, or fight it from the inside
out?

03:03:26.623 --> 03:03:28.071
LAURA: Maybe?

03:03:28.071 --> 03:03:33.082
TALIESIN: That's the most exciting Dwarven Forge
thing I'd ever want to see. The Godzilla

03:03:33.082 --> 03:03:34.153
interior.

03:03:34.153 --> 03:03:38.000
LAURA: We got to get inside of it.

03:03:38.000 --> 03:03:41.557
TALIESIN: It may be all it takes.

03:03:41.557 --> 03:03:44.629
LAURA: Are we on J'mon Sa Ord's back?

03:03:44.629 --> 03:03:50.587
MATT: Yes, right now it's large brass dragon
wings (flapping).

03:03:50.587 --> 03:03:55.215
TALIESIN: Neverending Storying our way to a
terrible death.

03:03:55.215 --> 03:04:01.726
TRAVIS: Can you detect if we're making up any
ground on your target? I'm talking to you, Vax.

03:04:01.726 --> 03:04:05.041
SAM: Liam, are we getting closer?

03:04:05.041 --> 03:04:12.489
LIAM: My brain's on Vecna, not on the city. Is
Vecna doing a ride-along? Is he still moving in

03:04:12.489 --> 03:04:13.741
the same direction?

03:04:13.741 --> 03:04:17.883
MATT: Yeah, Vecna's slowly traveling in that
southeast direction.

03:04:17.883 --> 03:04:19.740
SAM: Follow the tracks, then.

03:04:19.740 --> 03:04:26.475
MATT: All right. With that, you hear the booming
voice of J'mon once more, "Very well. Let us be

03:04:26.475 --> 03:04:32.700
"off." (whoosh) And goes into a fast-paced dive.
You all grab a hold of nearby dragon scale and/or

03:04:32.700 --> 03:04:38.093
loose bits of fur there are as it drives into this
huge dive, this gargantuan dragon.

03:04:38.093 --> 03:04:40.816
LAURA: Trinket's in the necklace for this part.

03:04:40.816 --> 03:04:42.862
MATT: I assumed as such.

03:04:42.862 --> 03:04:49.750
TRAVIS and LIAM: (scared bear noises)

03:04:49.750 --> 03:04:56.045
MATT: You see as the wyvern riders immediately
take this action and begin to swoop and follow

03:04:56.045 --> 03:05:03.566
suit, as well, following behind them. At this point,
you are the tip of the spear of this assault at

03:05:03.566 --> 03:05:09.541
this very moment. You begin to follow this
pattern, cross the pass, heading south-southeast,

03:05:09.541 --> 03:05:15.324
heading over and through different mountain
ranges. The higher you get, the wind gets a little

03:05:15.324 --> 03:05:20.266
more intense, and the cold begins to get more
biting. And J'mon dips down a bit to avoid having

03:05:20.266 --> 03:05:27.503
to thrust you into this very dangerous
stratosphere. The light in this area is very close

03:05:27.503 --> 03:05:32.006
to near dusk almost, with how much the sunlight is
blotted out by the cloud cover that has completely

03:05:32.006 --> 03:05:35.124
consumed the skyline, from horizon to horizon, on
all sides.

03:05:35.124 --> 03:05:41.570
MARISHA: I do a bit of a Gust spell ahead of us to
clear the path, give him a little more visual line

03:05:41.570 --> 03:05:42.616
of sight.

03:05:42.616 --> 03:05:49.300
MATT: "Thank you," you hear emanate from J'mon as
the cloud cover tends to spread a little bit and

03:05:49.300 --> 03:06:00.514
give a little bit of a good view. You travel on
for about 25, 30 or so minutes before Vex, Vax,

03:06:00.514 --> 03:06:10.768
and Keyleth, you glance around the bend of the
pass that you've just begun to curve around, and

03:06:10.768 --> 03:06:21.324
you see it: an impossibly immense entity, standing
hundreds and hundreds of feet tall. A gigantic,

03:06:21.324 --> 03:06:30.471
bulky mass of jagged rock, slowly walking on two
castle-width legs, each footfall sending a

03:06:30.471 --> 03:06:37.305
cloud-spray of earth into the air around it.
(crashing) Quaking the surrounding lands with a

03:06:37.305 --> 03:06:44.947
terrifying crack and rumble. As the back leg
lifts, sifting through the air, you can almost

03:06:44.947 --> 03:06:52.590
hear the air tear with a high-pitched whine, even
at this distance, as its sheer mass and speed in

03:06:52.590 --> 03:06:56.774
which it's cutting through, breaking the
atmosphere, slams down for its next step.

03:06:56.774 --> 03:07:07.935
(crashing) As you get a better view, the closer
you get, it resembles the earth elemental form

03:07:07.935 --> 03:07:15.890
you've seen Keyleth take many times, only
proportionally malformed, and terrifying on a

03:07:15.890 --> 03:07:25.683
scale you've never seen. Four colossal arms
swing from its torso, battering rams of shifting

03:07:25.683 --> 03:07:37.380
stone, each over 150 feet wide. The closer you
get, Grog, you sense a faint vibration in the

03:07:37.380 --> 03:07:39.394
Titanstone Knuckles.

03:07:39.394 --> 03:08:01.144
TRAVIS: Oh my fucking god. Just a note. These were
made from the heart of a felled titan. I don't

03:08:01.144 --> 03:08:03.213
think it's that one.

03:08:03.213 --> 03:08:05.143
LAURA: It could be! That one's dead!

03:08:05.143 --> 03:08:08.280
TRAVIS: That was sarcasm, but yeah.

03:08:08.280 --> 03:08:12.923
SAM: Are you going to take him, one on one?

03:08:12.923 --> 03:08:15.252
LAURA: Does that mean you can beat him up from the
inside?

03:08:15.252 --> 03:08:17.099
TRAVIS: Oh yeah, beat him up with his heart!

03:08:17.099 --> 03:08:18.658
LAURA: Yeah!

03:08:18.658 --> 03:08:26.466
TRAVIS: (stammering) Do I notice anything?

03:08:26.466 --> 03:08:36.144
MATT: Not in particular. You clap, and it sounds
booming, as it would. The closer you get, you

03:08:36.144 --> 03:08:42.413
sense this very faint vibration to them, as if
proximity keys you in, and even your simple

03:08:42.413 --> 03:08:48.177
mind, Grog, can gather that these were crafted
and made from whatever it is you see storming

03:08:48.177 --> 03:08:50.401
through that ravine.

03:08:50.401 --> 03:08:52.984
TALIESIN: Okay.

03:08:52.984 --> 03:08:58.473
LIAM: Do I feel Vecna riding on this guy's
shoulder?

03:08:58.473 --> 03:09:07.660
MATT: You sense the direction and distance of
Vecna directly where this entity lies. I would

03:09:07.660 --> 03:09:10.984
like you to make a perception check, please.

03:09:10.984 --> 03:09:12.202
LAURA: Do a what?

03:09:12.202 --> 03:09:21.332
MATT: Perception check. Just him for now as he's
focusing.

03:09:21.332 --> 03:09:23.564
LIAM: 27.

03:09:23.564 --> 03:09:27.587
MATT: You glance past as your proximity grows
closer and closer. One, you notice that there are

03:09:27.587 --> 03:09:34.873
beehive-type activity around the top where its
head would be. There is no massive head

03:09:34.873 --> 03:09:40.995
protruding, just the shoulder shelf where the top of it
becomes these four arms, and it's faced away from

03:09:40.995 --> 03:09:47.036
you, facing the way it's traveling, its arms
swinging wildly with each step, slowly. Its size

03:09:47.036 --> 03:09:55.096
is difficult for you to fathom at this distance.
It seems so big yet so small. As you get closer,

03:09:55.096 --> 03:10:00.862
you can see these bee swarm-like clusters
resemble creatures you saw in the Shadowfell not

03:10:00.862 --> 03:10:14.326
too long ago, and there atop the shelf of its
gargantuan torso, you see a cityline resting atop of

03:10:14.326 --> 03:10:23.834
this entity. There lies a portion of Thar Amphala,
moving with this gargantuan primordial earth

03:10:23.834 --> 03:10:36.525
titan, risen from below its long-held tomb.

03:10:36.525 --> 03:10:43.812
LAURA: I'm going to cast Pass Without a Trace on
us. It's not going to make any difference, but I'm

03:10:43.812 --> 03:10:45.215
going to do it.

03:10:45.215 --> 03:10:48.068
TALIESIN: Will that work on the back of a big
shiny dragon?

03:10:48.068 --> 03:10:54.485
TRAVIS: Another note, to be clear, these were
carved from the heart stone of a ruined earth

03:10:54.485 --> 03:11:01.597
primordial. When they're doing their thing, they
make me resistant to fire, cold, and lightning

03:11:01.597 --> 03:11:05.591
damage. So. That's good.

03:11:05.591 --> 03:11:17.183
MARISHA: Yeah. Theory time. Maybe. This primordial
is marching with Thar Amphala on its back to

03:11:17.183 --> 03:11:25.208
Vasselheim. If I were a god, wanting to prove that
I'm awesome and do a big miracle thing, I would

03:11:25.208 --> 03:11:27.860
drop a giant city on top of another city.

03:11:27.860 --> 03:11:31.247
TRAVIS: Or destroy the city and replace it with
that one.

03:11:31.247 --> 03:11:45.914
SAM: We can stop this, though. All we have to do
is beat the titan. I've got magic missiles that

03:11:45.914 --> 03:11:50.061
can do 1d6 damage.

03:11:50.061 --> 03:11:56.635
MATT: 1d4 plus one.

03:11:56.635 --> 03:11:59.649
SAM: We could be in business!

03:11:59.649 --> 03:12:04.491
TRAVIS: Listen. I know it seems really dire,
right? But the only other option besides attacking

03:12:04.491 --> 03:12:09.572
it, in my mind, is trying to get its attention.
Maybe lead it away from Vasselheim.

03:12:09.572 --> 03:12:14.210
TALIESIN: I think it's also, in theory, necrotic,
which means it can be turned.

03:12:14.210 --> 03:12:19.750
LAURA: That would be one powerful fucking spell.

03:12:19.750 --> 03:12:22.337
TALIESIN: We're going to have to do something.

03:12:22.337 --> 03:12:26.043
LAURA: Pike, how strong are you feeling right
now?

03:12:26.043 --> 03:12:30.913
MATT: You look back at Pike, who's clutching onto
the back of J'mon Sa Ord. Seeing this, her face

03:12:30.913 --> 03:12:35.589
pale white, eyes wide. She's like, "I don't
know."

03:12:35.589 --> 03:12:38.279
TRAVIS: It's all right, buddy!

03:12:38.279 --> 03:12:40.214
LAURA: You got it. You're a monster!

03:12:40.214 --> 03:12:50.779
MATT: (weakly) "I'm a monster! It's also a
monster!"

03:12:50.779 --> 03:12:55.348
(laughter)

03:12:55.348 --> 03:13:00.351
SAM: Should we land on the city on its back, or
should we try to fuck up the titan?

03:13:00.351 --> 03:13:06.036
LAURA: I think we should dive into one of the
beehive tunnels and stealth in. I think &lt;i&gt;we&lt;/i&gt;

03:13:06.036 --> 03:13:12.585
should still be stealth mode. J'mon can drop us
off. J'mon, you distract all of the city with all

03:13:12.585 --> 03:13:16.287
of your wyvern riders, as well, and we'll come in
from the bottom up, yeah?

03:13:16.287 --> 03:13:22.702
MATT: "I think that is a very sound plan.
However," and as the dragon's head turns and looks

03:13:22.702 --> 03:13:29.256
ahead, you can see some of these clusters of
gloomstalkers have broken away from the titan,

03:13:29.256 --> 03:13:35.469
swarming in your direction. You're about, I'd say,
a mile and a half away from it and gaining, only

03:13:35.469 --> 03:13:41.331
because you're pushing at full speed. You're
seeing now them breaking off into the clusters and

03:13:41.331 --> 03:13:43.939
you hear the distant (screeching).

03:13:43.939 --> 03:13:49.708
TRAVIS: I know we bamfed out here, but do we have
any idea how much time we have? How far away from

03:13:49.708 --> 03:13:51.412
Vasselheim we are?

03:13:51.412 --> 03:13:54.683
SAM: How far have we gone?

03:13:54.683 --> 03:13:57.061
MATT: Fom what you can tell, make a--

03:13:57.061 --> 03:14:00.735
TRAVIS: Don't make me make it. No, I'm ready.
Let's go!

03:14:00.735 --> 03:14:02.974
LAURA: I'm going to guess, too, because he's
asking out loud.

03:14:02.974 --> 03:14:04.607
MARISHA and TALIESIN: It's a good question.

03:14:04.607 --> 03:14:06.034
MATT: Make a nature check.

03:14:06.034 --> 03:14:11.632
MARISHA: Can I do it, too?

03:14:11.632 --> 03:14:12.892
TRAVIS: Negative two!

03:14:12.892 --> 03:14:17.982
(laughter)

03:14:17.982 --> 03:14:24.639
TRAVIS: My modifier, my &lt;i&gt;modifier,&lt;/i&gt; so 15. It was
17; I was excited.

03:14:24.639 --> 03:14:34.398
MATT: Not too bad! You haven't traversed this area
of the north side of Issylra before, but gathering

03:14:34.398 --> 03:14:41.841
based on where you were, seeing the sinkhole, and
the distance that Vax'ildan was giving you

03:14:41.841 --> 03:14:47.696
earlier, you imagine it's probably about 200 miles
or so away from Vasselheim.

03:14:47.696 --> 03:14:51.599
TRAVIS: Okay, we've got time. Not a lot.

03:14:51.599 --> 03:14:54.247
MATT: It has a very wide gait with each step.

03:14:54.247 --> 03:14:58.621
TRAVIS: But it's like Godzilla, right? It's like
(groaning, thud).

03:14:58.621 --> 03:15:04.242
MATT: Yeah! So you have time, but it's not 200
miles on normal person feet.

03:15:04.242 --> 03:15:06.025
TRAVIS: I mean, if he starts skipping, we're
fucked.

03:15:06.025 --> 03:15:18.769
LAURA: Hey, Keyleth. Do you have any of that Wild
Guide-- is that what's it called? That herb that scares away

03:15:18.769 --> 03:15:20.920
the undead.

03:15:20.920 --> 03:15:24.086
MARISHA: I do. Well, I grabbed some, so I can
cultivate more of it, yeah.

03:15:24.086 --> 03:15:26.308
LAURA: You should probably do that.

03:15:26.308 --> 03:15:29.819
LIAM: They're a mile and a half away, and they see
us, it looks like.

03:15:29.819 --> 03:15:33.128
MATT: Yeah, they're closing in, there's a short
time before they reach you. Remember, at this

03:15:33.128 --> 03:15:39.219
traveling speed, any sort of smoke-based censer
material is going to go right behind you like a flare.

03:15:39.219 --> 03:15:46.367
LIAM: Can we turn into clouds, Keyleth, and fly
off of our dragon ride and poof inside the titan?

03:15:46.367 --> 03:15:48.094
MARISHA: Let me see what I packed.

03:15:48.094 --> 03:15:52.060
TRAVIS: We'd be in the air, and not all of us are
so awesome in the air.

03:15:52.060 --> 03:15:57.427
LAURA: We could fall off this dragon's back real
fast.

03:15:57.427 --> 03:16:13.347
MARISHA: Okay. We could do Wind Walk. It's going
to take a minute to transform in and out. I also

03:16:13.347 --> 03:16:15.014
have Animal Shapes.

03:16:15.014 --> 03:16:18.496
SAM: J'mon, can you become invisible, by any
chance?

03:16:18.496 --> 03:16:32.443
MATT: J'mon, you hear the voice rumble, "I can,
but only myself. I could maybe affect a couple of you."

03:16:32.443 --> 03:16:35.200
SAM: I could affect a couple of us.

03:16:35.200 --> 03:16:36.498
LAURA: How many?

03:16:36.498 --> 03:16:38.913
SAM: Three.

03:16:38.913 --> 03:16:49.328
LAURA: That leaves quite a few of us left. Maybe,
J'mon, could you get--

03:16:49.328 --> 03:16:50.691
LIAM: Five?

03:16:50.691 --> 03:16:52.943
MATT: "I could muster about four."

03:16:52.943 --> 03:16:57.666
TRAVIS: That's enough. Three and four.

03:16:57.666 --> 03:16:59.786
LIAM: Pike.

03:16:59.786 --> 03:17:01.986
TRAVIS: I can't add.

03:17:01.986 --> 03:17:13.214
SAM: Or! I could make J'mon look like one of those
dark flappy things and make us look like undead

03:17:13.214 --> 03:17:14.231
creatures?

03:17:14.231 --> 03:17:16.846
LAURA: They probably have seen us coming, though;
they're on their way here.

03:17:16.846 --> 03:17:21.614
SAM: Yeah. Invisible, then?

03:17:21.614 --> 03:17:24.716
TALIESIN: At least we're a smaller target, at that
point.

03:17:24.716 --> 03:17:30.154
MARISHA: I can throw out a fog cloud and try and
fog us the rest of the way.

03:17:30.154 --> 03:17:32.329
SAM: We'll fly through it; it won't work.

03:17:32.329 --> 03:17:33.840
MARISHA: We're in clouds!

03:17:33.840 --> 03:17:36.336
SAM: If you do the thing, we'll keep going through
it.

03:17:36.336 --> 03:17:40.662
MARISHA: Oh. Yeah. That's a good point.

03:17:40.662 --> 03:17:44.215
TRAVIS: Invisible or change us. One or the other.

03:17:44.215 --> 03:17:46.999
LIAM: You could do invisible and I could fly as
fast as I fucking can away.

03:17:46.999 --> 03:17:51.154
MATT: (screeching) The cloud breaks ahead and you
watch as two gloomstalkers come diving down

03:17:51.154 --> 03:17:53.405
towards the back of J'mon.

03:17:53.405 --> 03:17:54.685
SAM: Let's do invisible!

03:17:54.685 --> 03:17:57.124
LAURA: I shoot one with an arrow.

03:17:57.124 --> 03:17:58.545
TALIESIN: I shoot the other one with a gun.

03:17:58.545 --> 03:18:00.242
MATT: Both of you guys, roll attacks.

03:18:00.242 --> 03:18:04.032
TALIESIN: It's okay. We're going at a speed that
it doesn't matter. Did that just happen?

03:18:04.032 --> 03:18:05.969
SAM: Yeah, I just knocked over a wine bottle.

03:18:05.969 --> 03:18:09.367
MATT and TRAVIS: A grape juice bottle.

03:18:09.367 --> 03:18:10.422
LAURA: 28.

03:18:10.422 --> 03:18:11.701
MATT: 28 hits.

03:18:11.701 --> 03:18:16.509
TALIESIN: (counting) 25.

03:18:16.509 --> 03:18:17.924
MATT: 25 hits, as well.

03:18:17.924 --> 03:18:23.547
TALIESIN: I should have said this. I was going to
burn a grit to drop.

03:18:23.547 --> 03:18:28.369
MATT: Right, I figured that was the case. One of
them gets shot with an arrow and as the impact

03:18:28.369 --> 03:18:32.486
hits, it shrieks but continues its dive. The second
one gets shot by-- which weapon was it?

03:18:32.486 --> 03:18:33.785
TALIESIN: Animus.

03:18:33.785 --> 03:18:39.243
MATT: With Animus. You watch as the detonation of
the spray of black from the impact of the bullet

03:18:39.243 --> 03:18:45.299
hitting. As it shrieks, its wings buckle from
underneath and it plummets about 30 or 40 feet or

03:18:45.299 --> 03:18:50.266
so and falls out of its dive. The one, however,
is still diving and it's going to go for the one

03:18:50.266 --> 03:19:00.256
that shot it with its arrow. Natural two. That's
going to be a 13. I'm pretty sure that doesn't hit you.

03:19:00.256 --> 03:19:01.531
LAURA: No, that doesn't hit.

03:19:01.531 --> 03:19:05.596
MATT: As it attempts to dive past you, you duck
out of the way, still nocking a secondary arrow.

03:19:05.596 --> 03:19:11.238
Its claws hits the back of the dragon scales. You
hear the scrape of it going across the back, but

03:19:11.238 --> 03:19:16.459
having no effect on the hard, armored brass
dragon's back. The gloomstalker then shrieks once

03:19:16.459 --> 03:19:20.042
more and takes back up into the clouds and
vanishes.

03:19:20.042 --> 03:19:22.515
LIAM: Did I get an attack of opportunity on it
with daggers?

03:19:22.515 --> 03:19:24.759
MATT: You can definitely attack it with daggers,
if you'd like.

03:19:24.759 --> 03:19:28.731
LIAM: Yeah, that hits. 29.

03:19:28.731 --> 03:19:30.404
MATT: That hits.

03:19:30.404 --> 03:19:33.147
LIAM: If my friend the dragon is against it, do I
get sneak attack?

03:19:33.147 --> 03:19:36.664
MATT: No. Sorry.

03:19:36.664 --> 03:19:40.470
LIAM: All right. That is 12 for that.

03:19:40.470 --> 03:19:43.479
MATT: 12 damage. How much damage did you do?

03:19:43.479 --> 03:19:44.663
LAURA: 15.

03:19:44.663 --> 03:19:52.567
MATT: As it shrieks and vanishes back into the clouds
above, you can see now the wyvern riders around

03:19:52.567 --> 03:19:59.647
are starting to charge in, as well. As you're rushing
now, you're maybe three-quarters of a mile from

03:19:59.647 --> 03:20:01.724
the exterior of this giant earth titan.

03:20:01.724 --> 03:20:03.076
LAURA: Invisible!

03:20:03.076 --> 03:20:09.186
MATT: All right. You complete your incantation in
time with J'mon, and the entirety of your party

03:20:09.186 --> 03:20:15.273
turns transparent and is now free from visual
perspective.

03:20:15.273 --> 03:20:17.904
LIAM: Did we get everybody?

03:20:17.904 --> 03:20:20.506
MATT: You did three?

03:20:20.506 --> 03:20:22.997
SAM: I can do four if J'mon can't.

03:20:22.997 --> 03:20:30.716
MATT: J'mon can do four. Well, Pike and J'mon
would be eight.

03:20:30.716 --> 03:20:33.167
SAM: Okay, so we'll do four and four.

03:20:33.167 --> 03:20:39.753
MATT: And with that, you all manage to disappear
and go into a dive. As soon as you all vanish,

03:20:39.753 --> 03:20:43.744
which is interesting because you disappear, and
suddenly your mount disappears, and all your

03:20:43.744 --> 03:20:48.502
friends disappear. So you're clutching on to what
you hope is still dragon scales and fur as you

03:20:48.502 --> 03:20:56.133
look down and see clouds, ground, mountains, and
eventual, plummeting death, were you not holding

03:20:56.133 --> 03:20:57.306
onto the back of the dragon.

03:20:57.306 --> 03:20:59.778
TRAVIS: (screams)

03:20:59.778 --> 03:21:04.013
TALIESIN: Wait, if our eyelids are invisible, does
that mean we can't even close our eyes?

03:21:04.013 --> 03:21:05.897
MATT: You can close your eyes.

03:21:05.897 --> 03:21:10.124
TALIESIN: No, it's too much. Too much. Not cool.

03:21:10.124 --> 03:21:14.174
MATT: I will say, because the enchantment doesn't
make you translucent, just invisible to the visual

03:21:14.174 --> 03:21:16.906
gaze, the interior of your eyelids would not be
affected by it.

03:21:16.906 --> 03:21:20.016
TALIESIN: Okay. That's my worst nightmare.

03:21:20.016 --> 03:21:23.012
MATT: Much like a Harry Potter invisibility cloak.
You can still see the inside of the cloak

03:21:23.012 --> 03:21:24.081
somewhat.

03:21:24.081 --> 03:21:26.179
TALIESIN: Yeah, no, I was just having a Clockwork
Orange moment.

03:21:26.179 --> 03:21:32.755
MARISHA: You make yourself more nauseous by
closing your eyes.

03:21:32.755 --> 03:21:34.168
TALIESIN: That's not true.

03:21:34.168 --> 03:21:37.932
MATT: As you go into this dive, you can hear the
clashing of wyvern against gloomstalker. You hear

03:21:37.932 --> 03:21:44.411
the yelps and the shrieks of two different bestial
cries. You hear shouts of humanoid and elven

03:21:44.411 --> 03:21:51.086
voices shouting as spears are tossed, arrows are
let loose, and this aerial fray begins. With that,

03:21:51.086 --> 03:21:57.005
you glance forward as the dragon comes out of a
dive, J'mon leading you towards this gargantuan

03:21:57.005 --> 03:22:12.436
entity. You can hear the further volume, the
(massive footsteps). Even slower than that,

03:22:12.436 --> 03:22:18.248
probably, based on the gait it has to walk and the
speed it's going. It is like watching a mountain

03:22:18.248 --> 03:22:22.397
with legs move. As you approach, what do you do?

03:22:22.397 --> 03:22:25.296
SAM: Do we see a clearing? A landing spot?

03:22:25.296 --> 03:22:32.167
MATT: You can make a perception check, guys. All
of you.

03:22:32.167 --> 03:22:38.483
LAURA: 25.

03:22:38.483 --> 03:22:40.277
MARISHA: 30.

03:22:40.277 --> 03:22:41.301
TALIESIN: 24.

03:22:41.301 --> 03:22:42.909
TRAVIS: Six.

03:22:42.909 --> 03:22:45.096
SAM: Eight.

03:22:45.096 --> 03:22:52.355
MATT: Eight, awesome. All right. Keyleth. You
guys, at this distance, it's hard to make out

03:22:52.355 --> 03:22:57.175
details. But Keyleth, you rolled a 30, which
according to 5th Edition is nearly impossible as a

03:22:57.175 --> 03:23:11.419
DC. So. You glance about and amongst the broken
rock exterior of this behemoth entity, you can see

03:23:11.419 --> 03:23:19.759
towards the base of its right leg, towards the
back, a faint trickle of water, like a waterfall

03:23:19.759 --> 03:23:32.172
of pee, probably. A trickling of a waterfall
that's flowing from its back leg area and then

03:23:32.172 --> 03:23:34.023
dissipating as it plummets into the air.

03:23:34.023 --> 03:23:36.201
MARISHA: That's it?

03:23:36.201 --> 03:23:39.157
SAM: Is it coming from the city or coming from the
titan?

03:23:39.157 --> 03:23:40.158
MATT: From the titan.

03:23:40.158 --> 03:23:42.815
MARISHA: He's leaking from the back of his calf.

03:23:42.815 --> 03:23:45.697
LAURA: Let's go in there, then.

03:23:45.697 --> 03:23:48.135
MARISHA: From the back of his hip.

03:23:48.135 --> 03:23:52.865
TALIESIN: Let's see if we can land on that burst
pimple, then.

03:23:52.865 --> 03:24:00.945
MARISHA: I don't think there's any landing. I
think there's going to be-- yeah. But you know

03:24:00.945 --> 03:24:02.863
what? Let's see what happens.

03:24:02.863 --> 03:24:04.750
LAURA: Let's fly in close to that waterfall.

03:24:04.750 --> 03:24:10.019
MATT: Okay, so you point this out to J'mon? All
right. You hear the dragon voice boom up once

03:24:10.019 --> 03:24:18.091
more. "Hold on!" Goes into an intense dive trying
to bring-- because previously you were about level,

03:24:18.091 --> 03:24:22.499
if not a little higher than Thar Amphala on the
top of the entity. J'mon goes into a dive towards

03:24:22.499 --> 03:24:28.037
the hip area that you point out. The wind is
pushing past you. You're holding on for dear life

03:24:28.037 --> 03:24:31.436
because any possible loss of grip not only is
going to loose you from the dragon, which is going

03:24:31.436 --> 03:24:40.430
to be hard to find you, as you're all invisible,
depending on the dragon's abilities, I guess. But

03:24:40.430 --> 03:24:45.296
as you begin to push down into this dive, I want
you all to make strength saving throws, please.

03:24:45.296 --> 03:24:50.540
LAURA: Oh god, strength? Jeez Louise.

03:24:50.540 --> 03:24:52.382
TRAVIS: Natural 20.

03:24:52.382 --> 03:24:59.459
TALIESIN: Natural 20!

03:24:59.459 --> 03:25:03.447
(cheering)

03:25:03.447 --> 03:25:09.705
(groaning)

03:25:09.705 --> 03:25:12.296
SAM: I got an 11.

03:25:12.296 --> 03:25:21.554
LIAM: I'm using my first Luck of the day. Oh,
that's worse. That is a nine for me.

03:25:21.554 --> 03:25:27.167
LAURA: God. A 22 for me. I know!

03:25:27.167 --> 03:25:32.504
MARISHA: This is a group success or failure thing,
right?

03:25:32.504 --> 03:25:39.563
MATT: In almost a poetic justice way, both Vax and
Keyleth begin to lose their grip, and with a

03:25:39.563 --> 03:25:46.632
sequence of moments, they both get blown off the
back of the brass dragon.

03:25:46.632 --> 03:25:51.121
LAURA: We wouldn't even know. Were they touching
each other? Tell me they were.

03:25:51.121 --> 03:25:57.592
MATT: You and Vax are currently now, no grip on
any dragon.

03:25:57.592 --> 03:25:59.229
MARISHA: Vax! Whisper!

03:25:59.229 --> 03:26:02.464
LIAM: I throw my dagger at that sound.

03:26:02.464 --> 03:26:04.263
MATT: Roll an attack.

03:26:04.263 --> 03:26:09.386
MARISHA: Wait, what?

03:26:09.386 --> 03:26:11.989
TRAVIS: That sounds like us.

03:26:11.989 --> 03:26:19.166
LIAM: Were you saying you were going to come to me?
There's the 18!

03:26:19.166 --> 03:26:22.291
MATT: With disadvantage, because she is
invisible.

03:26:22.291 --> 03:26:23.973
LIAM: That's a 20.

03:26:23.973 --> 03:26:26.306
MATT: What's your armor class, Keyleth?

03:26:26.306 --> 03:26:27.708
MARISHA: He hits.

03:26:27.708 --> 03:26:30.913
LAURA: Good, so you can bamf to her.

03:26:30.913 --> 03:26:38.691
LIAM: That's right. 12 plus psychic damage,
honey.

03:26:38.691 --> 03:26:42.009
SAM: You guys have a fucked-up relationship.

03:26:42.009 --> 03:26:46.838
MARISHA: Our entire relationship has been psychic
damage, baby.

03:26:46.838 --> 03:26:58.356
LIAM: 14.

03:26:58.356 --> 03:27:03.565
MATT: So you take 14 points of piercing damage.
However, as soon as the pain hits you, it's

03:27:03.565 --> 03:27:08.344
immediately allayed by the impact of Vax's arms
wrapping around you for dear life.

03:27:08.344 --> 03:27:11.814
MARISHA: (sputtering)

03:27:11.814 --> 03:27:13.604
LIAM: I'm kissing you already.

03:27:13.604 --> 03:27:18.106
MATT: You both are now tumbling and plummeting
through the sky.

03:27:18.106 --> 03:27:20.475
LIAM: Do you want to fly, or should I?

03:27:20.475 --> 03:27:23.245
MARISHA: Hold on! And I go giant eagle form.

03:27:23.245 --> 03:27:30.576
MATT: Okay. The giant eagle form takes flight. As
her wings extend, you realize you've been

03:27:30.576 --> 03:27:36.455
clutching on to the under down feathers. As soon
as the form takes, you grasp hold and climb back

03:27:36.455 --> 03:27:46.746
onto the top of the giant eagle. With that, you
both (whooshing). Now, here's an interesting

03:27:46.746 --> 03:27:52.485
question, because invisibility lasts until you do
an attack or cast a spell. It's a magical ability,

03:27:52.485 --> 03:27:55.418
I'm going to say that because it's a natural
effect, it will not affect the invisibility,

03:27:55.418 --> 03:28:00.224
especially because you're at a high enough druid
level. Specifically, shape changing is your thing.

03:28:00.224 --> 03:28:06.355
So I'll say you skirt under what would reveal
invisibility. You lose it, however, for attacking

03:28:06.355 --> 03:28:14.719
her. So now there's a Vax huddled on nothing,
full-on Wonder Woman-style invisible jet, riding

03:28:14.719 --> 03:28:29.198
through the sky. So as you guys coast in, the rest
of you hear J'mon go, "It appears we've lost some

03:28:29.198 --> 03:28:30.701
"passengers."

03:28:30.701 --> 03:28:36.585
MARISHA: No! Keep going! (cawing) Tell them! Keep
going!

03:28:36.585 --> 03:28:45.908
LIAM: We're all right. Everything's fine here.
Everything's fine. How are you?

03:28:45.908 --> 03:28:54.219
SAM: J'mon, they say they're okay. It's okay, we
can go.

03:28:54.219 --> 03:29:01.600
MATT: "Very well." Continues into the dive. You
guys are trailing behind at this point, but making

03:29:01.600 --> 03:29:07.712
your way down towards the hip region of this
entity, following the direction that Keyleth gave

03:29:07.712 --> 03:29:15.598
at her spotting earlier. As you guys get closer
and closer, you can see there is indeed a

03:29:15.598 --> 03:29:22.190
trickle of a waterfall that is dissipating, the
wind is so strong that it gets maybe 25 or 30 feet

03:29:22.190 --> 03:29:24.544
down before it gets scattered into droplets.

03:29:24.544 --> 03:29:26.416
SAM: Is it pee-colored?

03:29:26.416 --> 03:29:32.661
MATT: No, it is actually pretty clear water. You
do also glance, as you get closer, it appears to

03:29:32.661 --> 03:29:35.412
be emerging from some sort of an opening, like a
cavern entrance.

03:29:35.412 --> 03:29:36.992
LAURA: Yeah, let's head for the opening.

03:29:36.992 --> 03:29:42.100
MATT: So as you approach--

03:29:42.100 --> 03:29:47.470
LAURA: We have Pass Without a Trace!

03:29:47.470 --> 03:30:01.851
MATT: You do, but the flying man does not. So as
the rest of you make it up towards the side, and

03:30:01.851 --> 03:30:06.334
the wind is strong here, you can hear the impact
of each footfall, so deafening your eardrums

03:30:06.334 --> 03:30:14.611
almost shake and are in pain with each impact, the
bass of each footfall is immense. But you do see,

03:30:14.611 --> 03:30:20.342
interestingly enough, there is the waterfall
coming out of it. The waterfall is careening down

03:30:20.342 --> 03:30:31.525
a broken stone staircase. The opening is about
15 feet across and about ten feet wide. It

03:30:31.525 --> 03:30:37.400
looks like it was at some point attached, before
this creature arose, to another series of tunnels

03:30:37.400 --> 03:30:41.965
or wherever else this dwarven stronghold, this
series of vaults that were carved within this

03:30:41.965 --> 03:30:49.594
creature's body, extended beyond its torso. This
is one of the breaking points. As you glance back,

03:30:49.594 --> 03:30:55.770
you can see your brother coasting down about a
hundred or so feet away. You also watch as one of

03:30:55.770 --> 03:30:58.672
the large arms swings back.

03:30:58.672 --> 03:31:00.432
LAURA: No!

03:31:00.432 --> 03:31:02.959
MARISHA: I dodge it! I try and dodge it!

03:31:02.959 --> 03:31:10.442
MATT: I need both of you guys to make dexterity
saving throws. Actually, because you're riding

03:31:10.442 --> 03:31:14.341
Keyleth right now, it's going to be on the giant
eagle form, because you're clutching it.

03:31:14.341 --> 03:31:15.888
MARISHA: It's just on me?

03:31:15.888 --> 03:31:21.943
MATT: It's just on you. It's hard to avoid a
hundred-plus-foot-wide arm.

03:31:21.943 --> 03:31:33.120
LIAM: This is a save? Wait. This is a dex save,
right? I'm blessing Keyleth.

03:31:33.120 --> 03:31:36.807
MATT: As you see it coming? I'll say you have the
time because it's so immense.

03:31:36.807 --> 03:31:43.014
MARISHA: Add a d4, yeah? Four, yeah! Okay, 24
total!

03:31:43.014 --> 03:32:05.394
MATT: That's not enough. You were one away. It's a
25 DC because this is a giant fucking arm! Both

03:32:05.394 --> 03:32:18.549
you and Vax-- I don't have the dice for this, so
I'm going to have to use the app. You both suffer

03:32:18.549 --> 03:32:29.917
87 points of bludgeoning damage as the force of a
mountain slams into the side of your half-elf and

03:32:29.917 --> 03:32:36.337
eagle form.

03:32:36.337 --> 03:32:38.546
MARISHA: You said 87?

03:32:38.546 --> 03:32:40.481
MATT: 87 points of bludgeoning damage, yes.

03:32:40.481 --> 03:32:47.146
MARISHA: Okay. I immediately drop form and start
falling.

03:32:47.146 --> 03:32:50.303
MATT: Okay, any carryover damage, make sure to
mark that.

03:32:50.303 --> 03:32:53.614
LIAM: Does Uncanny Dodge affect this at all?

03:32:53.614 --> 03:33:00.977
MATT: Unfortunately, because you were relying on
her eagle maneuverability, no.

03:33:00.977 --> 03:33:05.063
LIAM: Okay. Well then, I shoot the wings out
immediately.

03:33:05.063 --> 03:33:12.372
MATT: Okay. The wings emerge as both of you begin
to plummet at this point.

03:33:12.372 --> 03:33:14.796
MARISHA: I'm okay.

03:33:14.796 --> 03:33:23.294
MATT: Keyleth? As you're plummeting, Vax, I need
you to roll a perception check.

03:33:23.294 --> 03:33:41.143
SAM: J'mon, they're fine. They told us they're
fine! They'll be here any second! Don't worry.

03:33:41.143 --> 03:33:44.165
TALIESIN: We did see this happen, right?

03:33:44.165 --> 03:33:50.766
MATT: You guys are right now hovering by this and
looking back. You watch this occur. You see Vax

03:33:50.766 --> 03:34:00.013
get smacked, fall, and then his wings shoot out.
Vax, roll a perception check. With disadvantage.

03:34:00.013 --> 03:34:08.762
TALIESIN: Roll really high, twice.

03:34:08.762 --> 03:34:15.855
LIAM: I rolled the same thing, so it's a 24.
Reliable talent.

03:34:15.855 --> 03:34:23.810
MATT: Strangely, you're able to see a slight shift
in wind to give you a brief moment to see where

03:34:23.810 --> 03:34:27.396
Keyleth's invisible, plummeting body is.

03:34:27.396 --> 03:34:29.531
MARISHA: Oh, I'm still invisible as I'm falling.

03:34:29.531 --> 03:34:36.737
MATT: Yeah, because you haven't cast a spell or
any attacks. So you manage to see this brief

03:34:36.737 --> 03:34:42.864
shimmer in space where the wind bends around her
reverting form.

03:34:42.864 --> 03:34:44.981
LIAM: I pick it up, grab it.

03:34:44.981 --> 03:34:50.039
MATT: You thrust downward with your wings. You
grab her body and manage to carry. You can feel

03:34:50.039 --> 03:34:54.292
her invisible body below you as you bring it back
up.

03:34:54.292 --> 03:34:56.192
LIAM: Punch me in the face. Punch me in the face
right now!

03:34:56.192 --> 03:34:57.424
MARISHA: (yelling)

03:34:57.424 --> 03:35:00.617
LIAM: Hey, beautiful.

03:35:00.617 --> 03:35:02.229
MARISHA: I'm sorry!

03:35:02.229 --> 03:35:04.815
LIAM: Let's get the fuck out of here! Do a barrel
roll.

03:35:04.815 --> 03:35:19.878
MATT: All right. Another giant arm swings, but
swings wide as it attempts to swing in the same

03:35:19.878 --> 03:35:25.266
place it did before. It does not seem to see the
two of you quickly approach the proximity of its

03:35:25.266 --> 03:35:32.307
torso. You hear this (zooming) passing over you by
about 30 or 40 feet.

03:35:32.307 --> 03:35:35.384
MARISHA: Oh, trying to go for J'mon?

03:35:35.384 --> 03:35:43.530
MATT: No, trying to go where you guys were. You
still have a visual point on it, so you direct and

03:35:43.530 --> 03:35:47.049
tug Vax by the hair and ears in the direction of
the path you saw.

03:35:47.049 --> 03:35:48.953
MARISHA: By the ponytail.

03:35:48.953 --> 03:36:03.895
MATT: Yeah, basically. And there, on the edge, you
can see J'mon Sa Ord there, wings flapping, as you

03:36:03.895 --> 03:36:08.500
guys rocket down and land right on the edge of the
footsteps. There's about a five-foot gap where the

03:36:08.500 --> 03:36:10.413
water isn't rushing past.

03:36:10.413 --> 03:36:15.676
MARISHA: Okay. I immediately cast Control Water
and suck it inside.

03:36:15.676 --> 03:36:25.927
MATT: Okay. The waterfall stops and bends upward
and is now being held. You guys have a row of

03:36:25.927 --> 03:36:29.962
steps ahead of you that are safe enough to land on
right now. They're still slick with water, but

03:36:29.962 --> 03:36:32.679
there isn't a rushing waterfall pouring over
them.

03:36:32.679 --> 03:36:34.861
LAURA: Can we see where to go to? An opening?

03:36:34.861 --> 03:36:36.837
MATT: You can see it ascends upward out of view.

03:36:36.837 --> 03:36:38.752
LAURA: Let's just go.

03:36:38.752 --> 03:36:41.412
TALIESIN: This is what's happening. This is who we
are now.

03:36:41.412 --> 03:36:50.389
MATT: J'mon, they swoop down and the giant dragon
claws (clattering) grapple onto the rock side of

03:36:50.389 --> 03:36:57.382
this large titan and leans forward, giving each of
you the opportunity to jump a very short distance

03:36:57.382 --> 03:37:06.582
over to these steps. As each of you make this
leap, J'mon disengages and flies up and says, "I

03:37:06.582 --> 03:37:12.824
"can only grant you so much, for I have many to
watch out here as we distract he who resides

03:37:12.824 --> 03:37:20.627
"above. However, take this." As the dragon head
descends, you see the eyes flare with energy as

03:37:20.627 --> 03:37:46.701
they cast Mass Cure Wounds. Ooh, two sixes and a
seven, not bad. All right, 12, 19. That's going to

03:37:46.701 --> 03:37:51.925
be 28 hit points healed to both of you.

03:37:51.925 --> 03:37:53.674
TALIESIN: That helps.

03:37:53.674 --> 03:38:01.901
LIAM: Yeah, as we were landing, the gashes all
over Vax's face started to heal up a little bit,

03:38:01.901 --> 03:38:04.683
but not all the way. Then suddenly they went even
further.

03:38:04.683 --> 03:38:13.224
MATT: "Be safe, and I'll see you on the other
side."

03:38:13.224 --> 03:38:19.185
LAURA: (fake-crying) See you on the other side of
the war.

03:38:19.185 --> 03:38:27.197
MATT: As you all stand on the precipice of this
opening that falls off into a drop, hundreds of

03:38:27.197 --> 03:38:33.617
feet to the rocky ground below, you can smell the
cold wind blowing through these caverns, emerging

03:38:33.617 --> 03:38:38.433
from this entrance you've found. As Keyleth holds
back the flow of this river, you glance up the

03:38:38.433 --> 03:38:45.210
dark, rising stairs, deep into the body of the
titan amongst the cursed vaults of this dwarven

03:38:45.210 --> 03:38:53.664
city, long abandoned, and begin your trek to
eventually meet your final conflict with the

03:38:53.664 --> 03:38:56.214
Whispered One. That's where we're going to end
tonight's game.

03:38:56.214 --> 03:40:14.377
(extended cheering)

03:40:14.377 --> 03:40:15.792
BRIAN: Keep it up!

03:40:15.792 --> 03:40:17.446
MATT: This is a little surreal.

03:40:17.446 --> 03:40:26.364
BRIAN: Big time. There's some people that we
really want to thank really fast. It's our crew,

03:40:26.364 --> 03:40:36.827
and it's the people who helped put this on for us.
So we want to thank-- I had the list but I left it

03:40:36.827 --> 03:40:47.140
backstage because I was too involved in what was
going on. Okay. Dani, Sax, Courtney, Ryan, Rachel,

03:40:47.140 --> 03:41:05.453
Ed, Jamie, Danny, Ben, Chris, Fernando, Audrey.
You guys. It takes literally six months to put one

03:41:05.453 --> 03:41:13.298
of these on. The amount of work and heart and love
that our crew has put into this has been

03:41:13.298 --> 03:41:18.868
incredible. You guys are incredible!

03:41:18.868 --> 03:41:47.456
(cheering)

03:41:47.456 --> 03:41:53.160
BRIAN: Thank you for waiting, thank you for
coming, thank you for participating! Don't worry,

03:41:53.160 --> 03:41:59.067
it's almost Thursday. Good night, GenCon!

03:41:59.067 --> 03:42:35.279
(cheering)

03:42:35.279 --> 03:42:46.787
SAM: See you guys tomorrow. Get some sleep. Thanks
so much; this was a lot of fun!

03:42:46.787 --> 03:42:59.162
MATT: So just a reminder, guys, those of you who
will be able to come to the signing tomorrow,

03:42:59.162 --> 03:43:02.335
we'll see you there. If you can come at least to
pick up some Scanlan stickers, I think it'll be

03:43:02.335 --> 03:43:13.629
worth your while. I'm going to post some images of
what they look like. I think you'll be happy. It's

03:43:13.629 --> 03:43:20.532
high time you got the fuck out and went to sleep.
Thank you guys so much for joining us.

03:43:20.581 --> 03:43:23.213
TALIESIN: What time is the signing? That's
actually a real question.

03:43:23.213 --> 03:43:34.058
MATT: Sorry, trigger warning on that question. Oh,
the signing is at 2:30, looks like, begins at

03:43:34.058 --> 03:43:38.688
2:30. Yeah, ticket says 3:00?

03:43:38.688 --> 03:43:44.455
BRIAN: Lucas Oil Field Stadium.

03:43:44.455 --> 03:43:49.237
MATT: (singing) My schedule is wrong! (speaking)
Pay attention to Geek and Sundry's Twitter for

03:43:49.237 --> 03:43:53.233
announcements. Anyway, thank you so much for
coming. Hope you had fun. We had a great time.

03:43:53.233 --> 03:44:02.530
(cheering)

03:44:02.530 --> 03:44:05.593
TALIESIN: No, don't touch that!

03:44:05.593 --> 03:44:09.885
